1
00:00:09,430 --> 00:00:12,190
Emergency transmission
from the Toraji Transport Network.

2
00:00:12,190 --> 00:00:15,710
This is an urgent request
for immediate assistance!

3
00:00:15,710 --> 00:00:18,070
This is an all-frequency appeal
for help.

4
00:00:18,070 --> 00:00:19,510
We're under attack!

5
00:00:19,510 --> 00:00:21,070
We've been hijacked!

6
00:00:21,070 --> 00:00:22,830
ALARM SOUNDS

7
00:00:22,830 --> 00:00:25,110
PANICKED SHOUTS

8
00:00:25,110 --> 00:00:27,230
All passengers down here!

9
00:00:27,230 --> 00:00:28,710
Marshals, to your posts.

10
00:00:32,230 --> 00:00:34,470
Who is it? Who's attacking us?

11
00:01:09,070 --> 00:01:12,430
Be careful.
It's all right, they're dead.

12
00:01:12,430 --> 00:01:13,990
Go through. Head down the train.

13
00:01:13,990 --> 00:01:15,950
There are more marshals.

14
00:01:15,950 --> 00:01:17,710
Secure passenger safety.

15
00:01:22,030 --> 00:01:24,030
What's happening to them?

16
00:01:25,590 --> 00:01:27,910
That energy... They're regenerating!

17
00:01:27,910 --> 00:01:32,150
All frequencies -
urgent appeal for help!

18
00:01:32,150 --> 00:01:33,950
Is there anyone out there?

19
00:01:33,950 --> 00:01:35,550
DOCTOR: Yes, there is.

20
00:01:35,550 --> 00:01:37,270
TARDIS THRUMMING

21
00:01:37,270 --> 00:01:39,390
We're unable to
materialise inside your craft.

22
00:01:39,390 --> 00:01:41,270
The Cybermen have
a blocking field in action.

23
00:01:41,270 --> 00:01:42,670
We're taking a different approach.

24
00:01:42,670 --> 00:01:44,950
Get out of there now!

25
00:01:45,990 --> 00:01:48,070
Ready?

26
00:01:48,070 --> 00:01:49,910
Ready. Ready.

27
00:01:57,790 --> 00:02:00,750
Leader, we have detected
a rescue attempt.

28
00:02:00,750 --> 00:02:03,030
Scans detect a TARDIS.

29
00:02:03,030 --> 00:02:04,950
The Doctor.

30
00:02:11,510 --> 00:02:13,750
DAN: Could you not have got
a less wobbly ladder?

31
00:02:13,750 --> 00:02:16,870
Why? It's perfect!

32
00:02:16,870 --> 00:02:18,710
Er...

33
00:02:18,710 --> 00:02:21,310
Well, ALMOST perfect.

34
00:02:21,310 --> 00:02:23,190
Tiny jump.

35
00:02:23,190 --> 00:02:24,750
Cool, right?

36
00:02:28,550 --> 00:02:30,070
Oh!

37
00:02:30,070 --> 00:02:33,070
Ah!

38
00:02:33,070 --> 00:02:35,710
Doctor!

39
00:02:35,710 --> 00:02:37,670
I've got you.

40
00:02:37,670 --> 00:02:39,590
Come on, Dan.

41
00:02:39,590 --> 00:02:40,790
What am I doing?

42
00:02:40,790 --> 00:02:43,070
I've got a date to get to.

43
00:02:47,590 --> 00:02:49,670
DAN YELLS

44
00:02:51,230 --> 00:02:53,070
Yeah! What a landing!

45
00:02:53,070 --> 00:02:55,070
9.9. Get in!

46
00:02:55,070 --> 00:02:57,310
Our boots are connected to
the electromagnetic roof.

47
00:02:57,310 --> 00:02:59,670
We're literally surfing
on a space train.

48
00:02:59,670 --> 00:03:00,870
Shut up, Dan!

49
00:03:00,870 --> 00:03:03,350
All right, Sheffield, just cos my
jump was better than yours!

50
00:03:03,350 --> 00:03:05,110
Dan, turn around!

51
00:03:12,670 --> 00:03:14,750
We need to wake the long-haul
passengers. There's no time.

52
00:03:14,750 --> 00:03:17,350
We can't just leave them.
You know what'll happen to them.

53
00:03:17,350 --> 00:03:19,430
We have to protect the cargo.
Keep moving!

54
00:03:19,430 --> 00:03:21,150
EXPLOSION

55
00:03:21,150 --> 00:03:25,350
Go with the passengers.
I'll hold them off.

56
00:03:25,350 --> 00:03:28,150
Where is the cargo?

57
00:03:28,150 --> 00:03:29,830
There's no cargo on board
this train.

58
00:03:29,830 --> 00:03:31,390
You lie.

59
00:03:31,390 --> 00:03:36,750
Identify the location
of the cargo carriage or be deleted.

60
00:03:36,750 --> 00:03:38,750
I'm not afraid of the Cybermen.

61
00:03:38,750 --> 00:03:41,790
We are more than Cybermen.

62
00:03:41,790 --> 00:03:44,030
We have evolved.

63
00:03:44,030 --> 00:03:47,270
We are your Cyber Masters.

64
00:03:56,670 --> 00:03:58,190
OK, two important points.

65
00:03:58,190 --> 00:04:00,430
Number one - find something to
hold on to.

66
00:04:00,430 --> 00:04:02,630
Number two - don't get shot! What?!

67
00:04:05,750 --> 00:04:08,310
I'm going to deactivate
the train's electromagnets.

68
00:04:08,310 --> 00:04:11,070
But aren't they keeping us
stuck to the roof?!

69
00:04:11,070 --> 00:04:13,070
Yeah, but not just us.

70
00:04:19,390 --> 00:04:21,150
Watch out!

71
00:04:33,670 --> 00:04:35,470
The train needs bringing
under control.

72
00:04:35,470 --> 00:04:36,910
We need to get the train to a halt.

73
00:04:36,910 --> 00:04:39,190
The controls are over there,
as I showed you.

74
00:04:39,190 --> 00:04:41,470
Don't lose my sonic.

75
00:04:41,470 --> 00:04:43,550
We need to find and keep
the passengers safe

76
00:04:43,550 --> 00:04:46,750
and find out what those
Cyber Masters want with this train.

77
00:04:52,470 --> 00:04:55,150
LASER FIRE

78
00:04:58,630 --> 00:05:01,790
Leader, the cargo has been secured.

79
00:05:01,790 --> 00:05:03,710
Open it.

80
00:05:05,150 --> 00:05:06,830
It's all right. It's all right.

81
00:05:06,830 --> 00:05:08,430
We're here to help.

82
00:05:08,430 --> 00:05:10,470
I'm the Doctor. This is Yaz.

83
00:05:10,470 --> 00:05:12,110
I can sort that wound out.

84
00:05:12,110 --> 00:05:13,830
Pass that medpack off the wall.

85
00:05:13,830 --> 00:05:16,870
All right, Dan, son,
just like she showed you.

86
00:05:24,030 --> 00:05:26,230
Dan? Whoops, sorry!

87
00:05:27,830 --> 00:05:30,550
Wrong setting.
Sorting it, hopefully.

88
00:05:36,830 --> 00:05:39,750
ANNOUNCEMENT: This is your space
train driver Dan

89
00:05:39,750 --> 00:05:42,350
reassuring you
everything is under control

90
00:05:42,350 --> 00:05:45,630
and we will be slowing
to a gentle stop momentarily.

91
00:05:46,830 --> 00:05:48,390
I'll deal with the Cybermen.

92
00:05:48,390 --> 00:05:50,310
They're not ordinary Cybermen.

93
00:05:50,310 --> 00:05:51,950
I know.

94
00:05:59,710 --> 00:06:01,510
Get away from that pod.

95
00:06:02,670 --> 00:06:06,550
Doctor, you shall
not disrupt our mission.

96
00:06:06,550 --> 00:06:07,950
Oh, I think I shall.

97
00:06:07,950 --> 00:06:09,470
Feel that slowing down?

98
00:06:09,470 --> 00:06:11,230
This train's under my control

99
00:06:11,230 --> 00:06:13,870
and reinforcements
will be here any moment.

100
00:06:13,870 --> 00:06:17,190
So whatever you came for, whatever
that cargo is, you've failed.

101
00:06:17,190 --> 00:06:19,590
EXPLOSION

102
00:06:28,470 --> 00:06:29,950
It's all right.

103
00:06:29,950 --> 00:06:31,310
Don't be scared.

104
00:06:31,310 --> 00:06:34,150
I'm the Doctor.
I'm going to protect you.

105
00:06:36,230 --> 00:06:38,910
The Doctor lies.

106
00:07:35,550 --> 00:07:37,870
KNOCK ON DOOR

107
00:07:44,070 --> 00:07:47,230
Father Grigori, I have
a message from the Tsarina.

108
00:07:47,230 --> 00:07:49,910
Your presence is urgently
required at the Winter Palace.

109
00:07:49,910 --> 00:07:52,390
The Tsarevich has been taken ill.

110
00:08:18,470 --> 00:08:19,790
Excuse me.

111
00:08:19,790 --> 00:08:21,030
Can I help?

112
00:08:21,030 --> 00:08:22,990
What's happened to this painting?

113
00:08:22,990 --> 00:08:25,510
It was taken down
for restoration work.

114
00:08:25,510 --> 00:08:27,750
Was there something wrong with it?
No.

115
00:08:27,750 --> 00:08:31,030
From time to time,
all the paintings need a little TLC.

116
00:08:31,030 --> 00:08:34,430
But this one was only restored
two months ago.

117
00:08:36,430 --> 00:08:39,270
It required
a little additional work.

118
00:08:40,550 --> 00:08:42,230
Did it?

119
00:08:43,630 --> 00:08:47,590
15 of the world's most well-known
paintings all been taken down

120
00:08:47,590 --> 00:08:51,310
pretty much simultaneously
and with no explanation.

121
00:08:52,710 --> 00:08:54,150
Where are you, anyway?

122
00:08:54,150 --> 00:08:55,830
Sorry, Ace. Say again?

123
00:08:55,830 --> 00:08:57,630
I said, where are you, Tegan?

124
00:08:57,630 --> 00:08:59,390
What day is it, Thursday?

125
00:08:59,390 --> 00:09:00,990
Romania.

126
00:09:00,990 --> 00:09:03,110
Somewhere near the Carpathians
or maybe in them.

127
00:09:03,110 --> 00:09:05,670
I'm losing track.
What are you doing there?

128
00:09:05,670 --> 00:09:09,430
There's a volcanic chain where those
three seismologists were last seen

129
00:09:09,430 --> 00:09:11,150
investigating a nearby earthquake.

130
00:09:11,150 --> 00:09:12,270
And did you find them?

131
00:09:12,270 --> 00:09:15,030
Disappeared off the face
of the Earth, just like the others.

132
00:09:15,030 --> 00:09:17,950
A dozen seismologists
and 15 paintings.

133
00:09:19,350 --> 00:09:20,630
There's something else.

134
00:09:20,630 --> 00:09:25,990
When I arrived at this cabin,
there was a package waiting for me.

135
00:09:25,990 --> 00:09:30,950
When I opened it up, there was
a Russian doll toy box inside.

136
00:09:30,950 --> 00:09:33,230
But there was also a card

137
00:09:33,230 --> 00:09:35,830
from the Doctor.

138
00:09:37,190 --> 00:09:40,030
Ace, I haven't heard from the Doctor
for nearly four decades.

139
00:09:40,030 --> 00:09:41,510
Yeah, all right, show-off!

140
00:09:41,510 --> 00:09:44,070
Just cos it's only
three decades for me.

141
00:09:44,070 --> 00:09:46,590
So what was the doll?

142
00:09:51,630 --> 00:09:54,870
A Cyberman! Of all the things.

143
00:09:54,870 --> 00:09:57,070
Why would the Doctor send me that?

144
00:09:57,070 --> 00:09:58,790
That's not a fond memory.

145
00:09:58,790 --> 00:10:01,830
It's not even a Russian doll

146
00:10:01,830 --> 00:10:03,670
and why send it to me now?

147
00:10:05,030 --> 00:10:06,550
I think we should go in.

148
00:10:08,310 --> 00:10:11,870
TARDIS THRUMS

149
00:10:16,110 --> 00:10:17,470
Back in time for your date.

150
00:10:17,470 --> 00:10:18,870
You're welcome.

151
00:10:18,870 --> 00:10:20,830
Should we pick you up again
in 24 hours?

152
00:10:20,830 --> 00:10:23,390
Yaz, you and I can try
and pick up the trail

153
00:10:23,390 --> 00:10:26,150
of where the Cyber Masters went
with that child.

154
00:10:31,990 --> 00:10:33,710
You don't have to come back for me.

155
00:10:36,990 --> 00:10:39,350
OK. What?

156
00:10:42,670 --> 00:10:46,790
I was one hand away from flying
off into space and suffocating.

157
00:10:48,070 --> 00:10:51,590
I don't want to push me luck
any further.

158
00:10:51,590 --> 00:10:53,390
I mean, all this...

159
00:10:53,390 --> 00:10:55,550
All this is amazing

160
00:10:55,550 --> 00:10:59,150
and I've had the most
incredible time.

161
00:11:00,750 --> 00:11:02,590
But it's not my life.

162
00:11:04,110 --> 00:11:07,590
And my life's
far from perfect, but...

163
00:11:07,590 --> 00:11:09,830
..I need to get back to it.

164
00:11:09,830 --> 00:11:11,710
I need to attack it.

165
00:11:11,710 --> 00:11:13,670
And I can now...

166
00:11:15,430 --> 00:11:17,150
..cos I've been with you.

167
00:11:18,670 --> 00:11:20,110
I get it.

168
00:11:21,270 --> 00:11:23,510
Life's important.

169
00:11:24,830 --> 00:11:26,510
Home's important.

170
00:11:36,190 --> 00:11:38,670
Yeah.

171
00:11:38,670 --> 00:11:40,510
My house.

172
00:11:40,510 --> 00:11:43,470
Looks like I'll be kipping
on my mum and dad's sofa tonight.

173
00:11:48,350 --> 00:11:50,190
See you again, Doctor.

174
00:11:54,390 --> 00:11:56,550
DOOR SHUTS

175
00:11:56,550 --> 00:11:59,270
Have I upset her?

176
00:11:59,270 --> 00:12:01,550
Not one for goodbyes.

177
00:12:01,550 --> 00:12:04,710
Whereas me,
I'm glad to see the back of you.

178
00:12:06,430 --> 00:12:07,790
I'll call you.

179
00:12:07,790 --> 00:12:09,750
I'll ghost you.

180
00:12:19,430 --> 00:12:21,830
TRANSMISSION: Doctor!

181
00:12:21,830 --> 00:12:23,110
No!

182
00:12:23,110 --> 00:12:24,630
Breaching transmission firewalls.

183
00:12:24,630 --> 00:12:26,630
Get out of my TARDIS!

184
00:12:26,630 --> 00:12:28,950
I mean you no harm.

185
00:12:30,310 --> 00:12:32,230
You'd be the first Dalek
to ever mean that.

186
00:12:32,230 --> 00:12:39,110
I have information critical to the
future of both humans and Daleks.

187
00:12:39,110 --> 00:12:43,950
It is imperative that you and I
meet immediately.

188
00:12:43,950 --> 00:12:46,230
I don't think so.

189
00:12:46,230 --> 00:12:50,990
I offer you the key
to the destruction of the Daleks!

190
00:12:53,190 --> 00:12:56,630
A Dalek invades my TARDIS with
a message offering to destroy

191
00:12:56,630 --> 00:12:57,950
its own species?

192
00:12:57,950 --> 00:13:02,470
I no longer believe
in the Dalek mission.

193
00:13:05,110 --> 00:13:08,270
Well, that's a new one.

194
00:13:08,270 --> 00:13:10,790
The Dalek machine was
created to ensure

195
00:13:10,790 --> 00:13:14,470
the survival of the Kaled race.

196
00:13:14,470 --> 00:13:18,990
Yet Kaled identity
has eroded over time.

197
00:13:18,990 --> 00:13:21,830
The Dalek mission has
changed to become

198
00:13:21,830 --> 00:13:24,470
the perpetuation of the Dalek race.

199
00:13:24,470 --> 00:13:31,230
Analysis concludes
we have lost the right to survive.

200
00:13:33,310 --> 00:13:37,510
Your Creator would
both be impressed and horrified.

201
00:13:37,510 --> 00:13:41,110
So you come to me as what, a spy?

202
00:13:41,110 --> 00:13:43,990
A Dalek incursion on Earth
is imminent.

203
00:13:46,470 --> 00:13:51,350
I offer you the chance to destroy
every Dalek before that attack.

204
00:13:51,350 --> 00:13:53,590
Why would I ever trust you?

205
00:13:53,590 --> 00:13:56,230
To save the lives of
billions of humans.

206
00:13:57,910 --> 00:14:01,590
I will communicate location
and time. You must attend.

207
00:14:01,590 --> 00:14:03,150
No-no-no, you don't order me!

208
00:14:03,150 --> 00:14:05,750
I am detected.
Transmission must end.

209
00:14:08,270 --> 00:14:10,110
YAZ: Who are you yelling at?

210
00:14:10,110 --> 00:14:12,230
ALARM SOUNDS

211
00:14:13,390 --> 00:14:15,590
The TARDIS has locked on to
the cargo trail.

212
00:14:15,590 --> 00:14:17,350
Now, where is that child?

213
00:14:18,710 --> 00:14:20,270
That data doesn't make sense.

214
00:14:20,270 --> 00:14:22,950
It's just outside Earth
in the year 1916.

215
00:14:22,950 --> 00:14:24,750
Why doesn't that make sense?

216
00:14:24,750 --> 00:14:28,670
Because I'm seeing one planet
too many in your solar system.

217
00:14:28,670 --> 00:14:31,550
And that extra planet is right
in the shadow of Earth.

218
00:14:42,030 --> 00:14:44,710
Tsarina, Rasputin approaches.

219
00:14:50,150 --> 00:14:52,230
It is good to see you,
Father Grigori.

220
00:14:53,590 --> 00:14:55,910
How is my son?

221
00:15:00,270 --> 00:15:03,470
Such a tiny injury and such
a terrible effect.

222
00:15:05,270 --> 00:15:08,390
His haemophilia is a cruel illness.

223
00:15:08,390 --> 00:15:11,350
I cannot help but think
that he has worsened

224
00:15:11,350 --> 00:15:14,990
ever since the arrival
of the second moon in the sky.

225
00:15:14,990 --> 00:15:17,910
An entire new moon.

226
00:15:17,910 --> 00:15:22,270
These special times must
not challenge our faith.

227
00:15:22,270 --> 00:15:24,670
They should strengthen it.

228
00:15:24,670 --> 00:15:26,350
I'm afraid for my son.

229
00:15:26,350 --> 00:15:28,790
I believe in the morning
he'll be much improved.

230
00:15:28,790 --> 00:15:30,630
But can you be sure?

231
00:15:31,830 --> 00:15:34,950
Are my eyes not full of certainty?

232
00:15:37,230 --> 00:15:38,590
Yes...

233
00:15:39,790 --> 00:15:41,390
..they are.

234
00:15:45,150 --> 00:15:48,990
My dear Tsar, this endless war!

235
00:15:50,510 --> 00:15:54,270
Have you made your decision to
send more troops or withdraw?

236
00:15:54,270 --> 00:15:57,030
It is so difficult.

237
00:15:57,030 --> 00:15:58,830
What would your advice be?

238
00:15:58,830 --> 00:16:02,710
My main concern is that you and your
family take some time away.

239
00:16:03,790 --> 00:16:06,150
A holiday.

240
00:16:06,150 --> 00:16:08,070
Very soon.

241
00:16:08,070 --> 00:16:09,870
Don't you think?

242
00:16:09,870 --> 00:16:11,390
Long holiday?

243
00:16:12,710 --> 00:16:14,310
Yes.

244
00:16:14,310 --> 00:16:16,350
Yes, I, erm...

245
00:16:16,350 --> 00:16:18,030
..I think so.

246
00:16:19,390 --> 00:16:20,550
Don't I?

247
00:16:20,550 --> 00:16:25,230
I will take care of your beautiful
Winter Palace

248
00:16:25,230 --> 00:16:28,950
and you will remain assured of
your one certainty.

249
00:16:31,510 --> 00:16:33,710
Which is?

250
00:16:33,710 --> 00:16:36,750
That you are the Master...

251
00:16:37,910 --> 00:16:40,190
..and I will obey you.

252
00:16:49,550 --> 00:16:52,910
TARDIS THRUMS

253
00:17:01,190 --> 00:17:05,270
Organic life converted
into metal on a planetary scale.

254
00:17:07,150 --> 00:17:09,390
Cybertechnology.

255
00:17:09,390 --> 00:17:10,990
Are they capable of this?

256
00:17:10,990 --> 00:17:14,870
There's Cybermen everywhere we go
right now, Yaz.

257
00:17:14,870 --> 00:17:17,950
Those ones on the train,
the Cyber Masters,

258
00:17:17,950 --> 00:17:20,070
they were created by the Master
on Gallifrey.

259
00:17:20,070 --> 00:17:21,910
Doctor.

260
00:17:39,550 --> 00:17:42,430
Stay here.

261
00:17:42,430 --> 00:17:43,990
Nope.

262
00:17:50,390 --> 00:17:52,590
It's not yours, is it?

263
00:17:52,590 --> 00:17:54,830
Yours from another time?

264
00:17:54,830 --> 00:17:56,750
In the future?

265
00:18:07,630 --> 00:18:09,630
I feel like I'm being taunted.

266
00:18:13,670 --> 00:18:15,230
DOCTOR GASPS

267
00:18:15,230 --> 00:18:17,430
The core of this TARDIS
has been lashed into the centre

268
00:18:17,430 --> 00:18:18,910
of the planet's metal structure.

269
00:18:18,910 --> 00:18:20,590
But why?

270
00:18:21,870 --> 00:18:25,710
The screen's showing another energy
source on the surface.

271
00:18:25,710 --> 00:18:27,550
Come on.

272
00:18:27,550 --> 00:18:30,510
Ah, there's a rudimentary cloaking
shield in operation.

273
00:18:30,510 --> 00:18:32,630
Soon fix that.

274
00:18:38,830 --> 00:18:41,990
The Cybermen have tethered
that child into this planet.

275
00:18:41,990 --> 00:18:44,070
It was registering
as an energy source.

276
00:18:44,070 --> 00:18:45,710
How is that child an energy source?

277
00:18:45,710 --> 00:18:48,270
Wait, there's more layers
to the shield.

278
00:18:48,270 --> 00:18:50,270
Oh, not just cloaking.

279
00:18:50,270 --> 00:18:52,870
It's a consciousness shield!

280
00:18:52,870 --> 00:18:54,870
A creature trying to evade capture,

281
00:18:54,870 --> 00:18:57,990
hiding behind a visual projection
shield, and this one shows us

282
00:18:57,990 --> 00:19:01,350
what we instinctively want to
protect, as a defence.

283
00:19:02,470 --> 00:19:04,230
So what is it?

284
00:19:04,230 --> 00:19:06,870
Oh, a Qurunx!

285
00:19:06,870 --> 00:19:09,630
One of the great mysteries
of the universe.

286
00:19:09,630 --> 00:19:11,910
I've never seen one before, Yaz.

287
00:19:11,910 --> 00:19:16,270
Sentient energy enough to power
planets and civilisations.

288
00:19:16,270 --> 00:19:18,030
They're so rare.

289
00:19:18,030 --> 00:19:22,150
A metal planet with a Qurunx
at the heart of it

290
00:19:22,150 --> 00:19:24,950
on the edge of Earth in the second
decade of the 20th century.

291
00:19:24,950 --> 00:19:26,750
Why?

292
00:19:28,310 --> 00:19:29,950
Desist!

293
00:19:29,950 --> 00:19:31,790
Ah, decided to show your face,
have you?

294
00:19:31,790 --> 00:19:33,510
Is this planet your doing?

295
00:19:33,510 --> 00:19:37,830
This structure is
the zenith of Cyberconversion.

296
00:19:37,830 --> 00:19:41,110
An entire planet transported here.

297
00:19:42,150 --> 00:19:44,270
You think I'm going to allow that?

298
00:19:44,270 --> 00:19:46,990
You will not be able to stop it.

299
00:19:46,990 --> 00:19:48,590
Oh, yeah?

300
00:19:48,590 --> 00:19:53,150
Why is that?
Your Master awaits, Doctor.

301
00:19:54,350 --> 00:19:56,910
Doctor, what does it mean by that?

302
00:19:59,950 --> 00:20:02,550
LASER FIRE

303
00:20:11,510 --> 00:20:14,110
TARDIS THRUMS

304
00:20:15,870 --> 00:20:17,270
Yes, what?

305
00:20:17,270 --> 00:20:19,310
TRANSMISSION: Doctor, UNIT needs
your help!

306
00:20:19,310 --> 00:20:21,750
Bit busy, Kate. Can it wait?
Absolutely not. Oh!

307
00:20:28,750 --> 00:20:30,990
Nice new building.
Thank you.

308
00:20:30,990 --> 00:20:34,790
Now, a dozen of the world's leading
seismologists have gone missing

309
00:20:34,790 --> 00:20:36,030
in the past two weeks.

310
00:20:36,030 --> 00:20:39,110
Plus 15 of the world's most
valuable paintings

311
00:20:39,110 --> 00:20:41,190
have disappeared from view.

312
00:20:41,190 --> 00:20:42,950
That's what you called us here for?

313
00:20:42,950 --> 00:20:45,630
Have you any idea what's going on
in outer space in 1916 right now?

314
00:20:45,630 --> 00:20:47,110
Strangely enough, no.

315
00:20:47,110 --> 00:20:49,590
Oh, also new freelancers.

316
00:20:49,590 --> 00:20:51,190
Don't be cross.

317
00:20:53,070 --> 00:20:54,950
Are you ready for this? No!

318
00:20:54,950 --> 00:20:56,630
Me neither.

319
00:20:59,270 --> 00:21:01,670
I believe you three
know each other of old.

320
00:21:01,670 --> 00:21:03,030
Oh, wow!

321
00:21:03,030 --> 00:21:06,230
You said a woman.
You never said young.

322
00:21:09,110 --> 00:21:10,910
Tegan.

323
00:21:12,310 --> 00:21:13,790
Ace?

324
00:21:13,790 --> 00:21:15,950
That is a good look on you,
Professor.

325
00:21:17,710 --> 00:21:20,070
What are you doing here?
I brought them in.

326
00:21:20,070 --> 00:21:22,950
I'm rebuilding our intelligence
networks with people who understand

327
00:21:22,950 --> 00:21:25,790
the problems Earth faces
from personal experience.

328
00:21:25,790 --> 00:21:28,190
It seemed pretty clear
where to start.

329
00:21:30,070 --> 00:21:33,110
So...how have you been?

330
00:21:33,110 --> 00:21:34,430
Like you care!

331
00:21:34,430 --> 00:21:36,830
Tegan, we discussed this.
38 years!

332
00:21:38,950 --> 00:21:42,430
I'm Yaz. The only one here who
doesn't really know what's going on.

333
00:21:42,430 --> 00:21:44,710
We used to be you, decades back.

334
00:21:48,950 --> 00:21:51,630
I see.

335
00:21:51,630 --> 00:21:53,230
Wow...

336
00:21:56,710 --> 00:21:58,710
So what was so urgent, Kate?

337
00:21:58,710 --> 00:22:00,990
This is why I brought you in.

338
00:22:03,070 --> 00:22:05,510
Let's start with the paintings.

339
00:22:07,190 --> 00:22:09,670
Mona Lisa, The Scream, The Hay Wain,

340
00:22:09,670 --> 00:22:13,150
Girl With A Pearl Earring,
The Last Supper -

341
00:22:13,150 --> 00:22:16,030
all of them and more
taken out of public view

342
00:22:16,030 --> 00:22:20,350
because all of them we've discovered
have been defaced.

343
00:22:20,350 --> 00:22:23,830
The face of Rasputin
inserted into every painting.

344
00:22:23,830 --> 00:22:25,470
Oh, no.

345
00:22:26,990 --> 00:22:28,950
That's not Rasputin.

346
00:22:28,950 --> 00:22:32,150
That's the Master.
What? What?

347
00:22:32,150 --> 00:22:34,350
Greetings, seismology fans!

348
00:22:34,350 --> 00:22:36,990
If you're craving answers
to life's little mysteries,

349
00:22:36,990 --> 00:22:39,350
my keynote address at the
International Seismology

350
00:22:39,350 --> 00:22:41,910
Memorial Conference is now
starting at a conference hall

351
00:22:41,910 --> 00:22:43,910
vaguely near you.

352
00:22:45,430 --> 00:22:47,390
Come feel the Earth move.

353
00:22:47,390 --> 00:22:50,430
Here's the pin. See you in a bit.

354
00:22:51,670 --> 00:22:53,390
So that's the Master now?

355
00:22:53,390 --> 00:22:55,830
1916, Rasputin,

356
00:22:55,830 --> 00:22:59,150
and the only person who would leave
a TARDIS that looked like mine.

357
00:22:59,150 --> 00:23:00,790
Hotel.

358
00:23:00,790 --> 00:23:02,830
3.2 kilometres from Mount Vesuvius.

359
00:23:02,830 --> 00:23:04,750
We've got a UNIT base near Naples.

360
00:23:04,750 --> 00:23:06,110
I'll get you local support.

361
00:23:06,110 --> 00:23:09,750
Sorry, dealing with multiple
somethings.

362
00:23:09,750 --> 00:23:11,230
It's good to see you both.

363
00:23:11,230 --> 00:23:12,470
Ow!

364
00:23:12,470 --> 00:23:15,870
You gave me an electric shock.
Sorry. My bad. I promise.

365
00:23:15,870 --> 00:23:18,270
I'm coming back. Ow!

366
00:23:18,270 --> 00:23:20,150
Oh, you are really staticky.

367
00:23:22,030 --> 00:23:24,590
We'll be back. Come on, Yaz.

368
00:23:27,230 --> 00:23:29,830
I think I handled that quite well.

369
00:23:29,830 --> 00:23:32,310
TARDIS THRUMS

370
00:23:33,350 --> 00:23:36,870
If we correlate the
latest tremor detection data

371
00:23:36,870 --> 00:23:39,830
with the aforementioned ground
deformation measurements,

372
00:23:39,830 --> 00:23:43,230
cross-referencing the increase
in volcanic gas emissions

373
00:23:43,230 --> 00:23:46,190
and rising magma levels, we know...
Doctor, look!

374
00:23:46,190 --> 00:23:50,070
..ladies and gentlemen, that it
would only take the slightest

375
00:23:50,070 --> 00:23:52,150
tectonic pressure...

376
00:23:56,830 --> 00:23:59,230
Do you like my seismologist
collection?

377
00:23:59,230 --> 00:24:00,790
I think I've got the whole set now.

378
00:24:00,790 --> 00:24:03,310
All right,
I followed your breadcrumb trail.

379
00:24:03,310 --> 00:24:05,470
Some people think you're Rasputin,

380
00:24:05,470 --> 00:24:09,030
you've got a TARDIS on a metal
planet with a stolen Qurunx,

381
00:24:09,030 --> 00:24:12,350
guarded by your Cyber Masters
in 1916.

382
00:24:12,350 --> 00:24:15,190
Now, do I win a prize if I guess
how this all fits together

383
00:24:15,190 --> 00:24:17,350
or are you just going to tell me
why you're grandstanding?

384
00:24:17,350 --> 00:24:19,550
Be patient. We'll get there.

385
00:24:19,550 --> 00:24:21,870
How did you even escape
from Gallifrey?

386
00:24:21,870 --> 00:24:23,990
Magnificent attention to detail.

387
00:24:23,990 --> 00:24:26,710
I'm a seismologist now.

388
00:24:26,710 --> 00:24:29,150
You killed all these people.

389
00:24:29,150 --> 00:24:31,030
For what?

390
00:24:34,390 --> 00:24:38,590
To give you simple, fair warning.

391
00:24:41,910 --> 00:24:47,030
Leave Earth now, Doctor,
or it will be the death of you,

392
00:24:47,030 --> 00:24:50,670
because really, honestly, truly,

393
00:24:50,670 --> 00:24:52,870
this is the day you die.

394
00:24:52,870 --> 00:24:56,390
No...not just die.

395
00:24:56,390 --> 00:25:00,150
This is the day
you are erased from existence...

396
00:25:01,510 --> 00:25:03,190
..forever!

397
00:25:08,630 --> 00:25:11,750
I know, a bit of a
conversation stopper.

398
00:25:11,750 --> 00:25:13,910
Awkward, right, Yaz?

399
00:25:15,230 --> 00:25:17,110
Do you see what I've done?

400
00:25:17,110 --> 00:25:20,070
I was so clever because I can give
her this warning,

401
00:25:20,070 --> 00:25:22,230
but we both know she won't leave.

402
00:25:22,230 --> 00:25:24,150
She can't, not now
I've said that to her,

403
00:25:24,150 --> 00:25:26,910
and yet she knows she should,
because she also knows

404
00:25:26,910 --> 00:25:28,510
I don't make empty threats.

405
00:25:28,510 --> 00:25:33,350
I can absolutely, categorically,
pinky-promisey confirm

406
00:25:33,350 --> 00:25:36,030
this is no empty threat.

407
00:25:36,030 --> 00:25:37,630
DOOR SLAMS

408
00:25:37,630 --> 00:25:40,190
SOLDIERS: Go! Go! Go! Go!

409
00:25:40,190 --> 00:25:41,910
Oh, oh!

410
00:25:41,910 --> 00:25:44,430
You brought soldiers!

411
00:25:44,430 --> 00:25:46,190
Are these for me?

412
00:25:46,190 --> 00:25:48,110
Oh, you shouldn't have.

413
00:25:48,110 --> 00:25:49,390
Is this rendition?

414
00:25:49,390 --> 00:25:51,830
I've always wanted to be
renditioned. Or is it rendered?

415
00:25:51,830 --> 00:25:54,550
Ooh, gentle, gentle, gentle, boys!

416
00:25:54,550 --> 00:25:56,550
Am I going to UNIT?

417
00:25:56,550 --> 00:25:59,190
I hope I'm going to UNIT.

418
00:25:59,190 --> 00:26:00,950
Give her a gun.

419
00:26:00,950 --> 00:26:03,110
What?

420
00:26:03,110 --> 00:26:06,790
Cover him. We're going to take
him in the TARDIS.

421
00:26:06,790 --> 00:26:08,350
Take the gun.

422
00:26:08,350 --> 00:26:09,750
Yaz, she must be worried.

423
00:26:09,750 --> 00:26:12,270
Thought she didn't like guns.

424
00:26:12,270 --> 00:26:14,230
Fine.

425
00:26:16,790 --> 00:26:18,790
Do you even know how to use that,
love?

426
00:26:18,790 --> 00:26:21,470
Don't you worry,
I've had weapons training.

427
00:26:21,470 --> 00:26:23,390
Now move!

428
00:26:24,630 --> 00:26:27,110
Great chat. Good meeting.
Thank you all.

429
00:26:27,110 --> 00:26:29,190
Clear up the tiny bodies

430
00:26:29,190 --> 00:26:32,070
and inform the loved ones for me,
would you?

431
00:26:34,950 --> 00:26:37,350
You're not going to shoot me.

432
00:26:37,350 --> 00:26:39,030
Not in her TARDIS.
Think of the mess!

433
00:26:39,030 --> 00:26:40,510
Just in case you're wondering,

434
00:26:40,510 --> 00:26:42,990
all this
I'm-messing-with-your-mind chat,

435
00:26:42,990 --> 00:26:45,590
I've heard worse on a Friday
night in Sheffield.

436
00:26:45,590 --> 00:26:48,150
HE LAUGHS

437
00:26:51,510 --> 00:26:53,670
Can I let you in on a little secret?

438
00:26:54,950 --> 00:26:56,790
It's OK, it's OK.

439
00:26:59,430 --> 00:27:01,830
I ingested the Cyberium -

440
00:27:01,830 --> 00:27:04,710
the battle AI of the Cybermen.

441
00:27:04,710 --> 00:27:06,590
I'm so many steps ahead.

442
00:27:06,590 --> 00:27:08,710
I can see it all...

443
00:27:08,710 --> 00:27:11,110
..right through to all our ends.

444
00:27:12,910 --> 00:27:16,470
I'm sorry, Yaz, this is going to
be very, very painful.

445
00:27:16,470 --> 00:27:18,710
In your dreams, mate.

446
00:27:18,710 --> 00:27:20,470
Yeah.

447
00:27:20,470 --> 00:27:22,830
UNIT will keep you under
armed guard, while I get rid of

448
00:27:22,830 --> 00:27:25,230
all the mess you've been scattering
around the place.

449
00:27:25,230 --> 00:27:26,990
Whatever you want.

450
00:27:28,230 --> 00:27:30,990
I'm in her head.

451
00:27:30,990 --> 00:27:33,070
I said I'm in your head, dear.

452
00:27:34,070 --> 00:27:36,310
ALARM SOUNDS

453
00:27:37,910 --> 00:27:40,510
Aren't those Dalek symbols?

454
00:27:40,510 --> 00:27:42,030
What are they, coordinates?

455
00:27:42,030 --> 00:27:44,350
Why are you getting
messages from Daleks?

456
00:27:44,350 --> 00:27:46,230
Why is she getting messages
from Daleks?

457
00:27:46,230 --> 00:27:48,670
I'm sure there's a good reason.

458
00:27:48,670 --> 00:27:50,670
Let's hope so.

459
00:27:53,310 --> 00:27:57,030
Status report - Inston-Vee Vinder
now exiting the wormhole.

460
00:27:57,030 --> 00:28:00,830
I've survived, and I'm detecting a
life signal from the missing Qurunx,

461
00:28:00,830 --> 00:28:03,830
but the wormhole is playing
havoc with the ship.

462
00:28:03,830 --> 00:28:08,190
In summary, wormhole navigation
was a really bad idea!

463
00:28:08,190 --> 00:28:10,270
LOUD CRASH

464
00:28:22,390 --> 00:28:23,710
OK...

465
00:28:25,190 --> 00:28:27,270
Let's start with the good news.

466
00:28:27,270 --> 00:28:29,990
The ship did accurately predict
the wormhole

467
00:28:29,990 --> 00:28:32,630
and managed to surf it
with me inside.

468
00:28:32,630 --> 00:28:34,430
Good news part two.

469
00:28:34,430 --> 00:28:37,030
It did lead me to
the missing Qurunx,

470
00:28:37,030 --> 00:28:41,590
so I guess we could say
mission partially successful?

471
00:28:42,670 --> 00:28:44,710
Except...

472
00:28:44,710 --> 00:28:47,870
..apparently it's connected to some
control system on a planet

473
00:28:47,870 --> 00:28:50,750
that shouldn't even be here,
according to the charts.

474
00:28:52,790 --> 00:28:57,190
Oh, and I have a ship problem
in that it's broken.

475
00:28:58,310 --> 00:29:00,110
Thanks, wormhole.

476
00:29:05,110 --> 00:29:06,790
Wait...

477
00:29:08,990 --> 00:29:10,590
Put him in the bunker.

478
00:29:10,590 --> 00:29:12,750
Constant monitoring,
full security detail.

479
00:29:12,750 --> 00:29:14,230
Ooh, the bunker!

480
00:29:14,230 --> 00:29:16,870
That sounds nice! I love a bunker!

481
00:29:16,870 --> 00:29:18,350
Anybody want to join me?

482
00:29:18,350 --> 00:29:20,710
Bunk-up in the bunker?

483
00:29:20,710 --> 00:29:22,950
Your dad was an idiot.

484
00:29:26,470 --> 00:29:29,470
Oh, Tegan Jovanka!

485
00:29:29,470 --> 00:29:32,190
How's your Auntie Vanessa? Do you
keep her in a little doll's house?

486
00:29:32,190 --> 00:29:34,790
I'm going to enjoy watching you
locked up in a tiny cell.

487
00:29:34,790 --> 00:29:36,110
That's right, you tell me.

488
00:29:36,110 --> 00:29:38,030
And Ace!

489
00:29:38,030 --> 00:29:40,470
Or should I say Dorothy?

490
00:29:40,470 --> 00:29:42,390
Didn't the Doctor ditch you?

491
00:29:42,390 --> 00:29:45,310
No? Little fallout
with your Machiavellian maestro?

492
00:29:45,310 --> 00:29:48,070
Last time I saw you,
you were half cat.

493
00:29:49,230 --> 00:29:50,950
A man's allowed to experiment.

494
00:29:50,950 --> 00:29:53,550
Take him away.
Yes, yes, take me away!

495
00:29:53,550 --> 00:29:56,110
You'll all feel safer then
with me in the building.

496
00:29:58,510 --> 00:30:01,150
You're not staying, Doctor?

497
00:30:01,150 --> 00:30:03,550
You're not going to leave them
alone, are you...

498
00:30:03,550 --> 00:30:05,310
..while you go Dalek hunting?

499
00:30:05,310 --> 00:30:06,670
Whoo!

500
00:30:06,670 --> 00:30:08,430
Ace, Tegan, I need you to stay here

501
00:30:08,430 --> 00:30:09,710
and monitor the Master.

502
00:30:09,710 --> 00:30:10,910
We won't be long.

503
00:30:10,910 --> 00:30:13,110
ACE: Professor,
where are you going?

504
00:30:13,110 --> 00:30:16,070
She really doesn't want us
back in there.

505
00:30:18,310 --> 00:30:19,630
Wow.

506
00:30:22,870 --> 00:30:24,910
Love what you've done
with the place.

507
00:30:29,110 --> 00:30:32,270
Darling, I don't seem to have
the room-service menu.

508
00:30:32,270 --> 00:30:34,070
Only, I have allergies.

509
00:30:34,070 --> 00:30:35,510
I'm human-intolerant.

510
00:30:35,510 --> 00:30:36,910
LOCK CLANGS

511
00:30:36,910 --> 00:30:38,150
No?

512
00:30:38,150 --> 00:30:40,750
Just trying to lighten the tone
before you all die.

513
00:30:45,790 --> 00:30:46,830
YAZ: Doctor!

514
00:30:46,830 --> 00:30:48,350
Stop for a second.

515
00:30:48,350 --> 00:30:49,830
I can't keep doing this with you -

516
00:30:49,830 --> 00:30:52,310
running from one place
to the next, never explaining.

517
00:30:52,310 --> 00:30:53,470
Sorry, no time.

518
00:30:54,510 --> 00:30:56,590
Make time.

519
00:30:57,990 --> 00:30:59,670
Daleks...

520
00:30:59,670 --> 00:31:03,030
On the same day as the Master
and Cybermen.

521
00:31:03,030 --> 00:31:06,310
I know. They're either separate
problems, or all part of

522
00:31:06,310 --> 00:31:09,230
one bigger scheme.
He doesn't have that power.

523
00:31:09,230 --> 00:31:11,470
He couldn't corral Daleks
and Cybermen...

524
00:31:13,270 --> 00:31:14,590
Could he?

525
00:31:14,590 --> 00:31:16,510
It's all happening so fast.

526
00:31:16,510 --> 00:31:18,070
Ooh!

527
00:31:18,070 --> 00:31:20,190
Very sorry.
I am really staticky today.

528
00:31:20,190 --> 00:31:21,510
SONIC WHIRS

529
00:31:21,510 --> 00:31:22,950
You're going to meet a Dalek.

530
00:31:22,950 --> 00:31:25,110
Has it never occurred to you
that it could be a trap?

531
00:31:25,110 --> 00:31:26,150
Of course it has.

532
00:31:26,150 --> 00:31:28,190
But there's about to be
a Dalek attack on Earth.

533
00:31:28,190 --> 00:31:30,430
And the one that tipped me off
said it has information

534
00:31:30,430 --> 00:31:32,590
which could help us
stop the Daleks,

535
00:31:32,590 --> 00:31:35,950
but not just now -
all Daleks, for ever.

536
00:31:35,950 --> 00:31:37,830
It's a calculated risk.

537
00:31:37,830 --> 00:31:40,270
And it's one I have to take.

538
00:31:42,470 --> 00:31:44,150
TARDIS THRUMS

539
00:31:52,030 --> 00:31:54,590
I'll take down there.
Meet you back here.

540
00:31:54,590 --> 00:31:55,950
Be careful.

541
00:31:57,910 --> 00:32:00,070
I'm supposed to be
the one saying that to you.

542
00:32:13,670 --> 00:32:17,470
I am surprised, Doctor.
I was not sure you would come.

543
00:32:17,470 --> 00:32:18,710
Well, I did.

544
00:32:18,710 --> 00:32:20,870
Now give me the information
you promised.

545
00:32:20,870 --> 00:32:23,310
All data is
contained within my casing.

546
00:32:23,310 --> 00:32:25,150
You must be fast.

547
00:32:25,150 --> 00:32:27,030
This will extract
all the information.

548
00:32:27,030 --> 00:32:29,630
You're really going to let me
do this?

549
00:32:29,630 --> 00:32:31,270
I am.

550
00:32:34,110 --> 00:32:37,310
Data transfer in progress.

551
00:32:38,550 --> 00:32:40,430
I have betrayed my species.

552
00:32:40,430 --> 00:32:43,270
You must ensure
they are destroyed.

553
00:32:43,270 --> 00:32:44,790
DALEK: Testing complete.

554
00:32:44,790 --> 00:32:47,830
All systems are in place

555
00:32:47,830 --> 00:32:50,950
and operating
at maximum efficiency.

556
00:32:50,950 --> 00:32:53,190
We are ready. No...

557
00:32:53,190 --> 00:32:54,990
They're already here.

558
00:32:56,190 --> 00:32:57,750
Seismology.

559
00:32:57,750 --> 00:32:59,670
Volcanoes.

560
00:32:59,670 --> 00:33:00,950
Daleks.

561
00:33:02,070 --> 00:33:03,750
And the Master.

562
00:33:03,750 --> 00:33:04,870
No...

563
00:33:04,870 --> 00:33:06,830
This is not good news.

564
00:33:08,230 --> 00:33:11,150
I'll get surveillance up
on the Master's cell.

565
00:33:11,150 --> 00:33:13,750
We can take turns watching.
Whatever he's up to,

566
00:33:13,750 --> 00:33:16,190
he can't do much
from a UNIT prison cell.

567
00:33:16,190 --> 00:33:18,350
I really thought
I'd seen the last of him.

568
00:33:18,350 --> 00:33:19,790
CLATTER

569
00:33:23,150 --> 00:33:24,350
Ace?

570
00:33:24,350 --> 00:33:25,430
The toy...

571
00:33:29,350 --> 00:33:30,390
MASTER: Oh!

572
00:33:30,390 --> 00:33:32,470
Didn't it want to stay
inside your bag?

573
00:33:32,470 --> 00:33:33,950
Oh, Tegan.

574
00:33:35,230 --> 00:33:37,270
Do you really think
the Doctor cared enough

575
00:33:37,270 --> 00:33:39,990
to send you
even one meagre toy?

576
00:33:39,990 --> 00:33:41,670
How's he doing that?

577
00:33:41,670 --> 00:33:43,670
The Doctor
didn't send you that,

578
00:33:43,670 --> 00:33:45,630
I did...

579
00:33:45,630 --> 00:33:48,670
..knowing what
you would do with it.

580
00:33:49,710 --> 00:33:51,790
You'd keep it so close to you

581
00:33:51,790 --> 00:33:53,750
because you have nothing else.

582
00:33:53,750 --> 00:33:56,550
Do you know the great thing
about tissue compression?

583
00:33:57,950 --> 00:34:00,670
It also works in reverse.

584
00:34:04,470 --> 00:34:06,870
That ain't just any Cyberman.

585
00:34:06,870 --> 00:34:09,110
It's a Russian doll.

586
00:34:17,470 --> 00:34:20,750
Oh! And say hello
to my friend Ashad.

587
00:34:20,750 --> 00:34:23,630
I killed him once,
but he's forgiven me now.

588
00:34:23,630 --> 00:34:24,830
Tegan!

589
00:34:23,630 --> 00:34:24,830
MASTER LAUGHS

590
00:34:29,870 --> 00:34:31,710
Gold bullets, tin-heads!

591
00:34:31,710 --> 00:34:33,310
Did you think UNIT
wouldn't be ready?

592
00:34:35,750 --> 00:34:37,590
Why isn't it working?

593
00:34:37,590 --> 00:34:41,870
We long ago
developed resistance to gold.

594
00:34:41,870 --> 00:34:42,990
BOTH: Run!

595
00:34:42,990 --> 00:34:45,270
Oh, run!

596
00:34:42,990 --> 00:34:45,270
MASTER LAUGHS

597
00:34:45,270 --> 00:34:47,430
Run! Oh, look at them.

598
00:34:49,870 --> 00:34:52,590
KATE ON TANNOY: All units,
full combat protocols.

599
00:34:52,590 --> 00:34:54,430
UNIT is under attack.

600
00:34:54,430 --> 00:34:58,830
I repeat, UNIT is under attack
from Cybermen.

601
00:35:22,110 --> 00:35:23,670
HE GRUNTS

602
00:35:25,230 --> 00:35:27,430
I am so glad I cloned you.

603
00:35:29,430 --> 00:35:31,270
Every detail...

604
00:35:31,270 --> 00:35:33,390
..paying off.

605
00:35:37,510 --> 00:35:39,150
Such a good plan.

606
00:35:42,510 --> 00:35:44,430
Data transfer almost complete.

607
00:35:44,430 --> 00:35:45,870
We are detected!

608
00:35:45,870 --> 00:35:49,270
DALEK COMMANDER:
Stay where you are, Doctor.

609
00:35:49,270 --> 00:35:51,270
You have no escape.

610
00:35:51,270 --> 00:35:52,830
Was this your plan?

611
00:35:52,830 --> 00:35:54,590
To lure me in
and then betray me?

612
00:35:54,590 --> 00:35:58,510
I did not betray you.
The traitor speaks the truth.

613
00:35:58,510 --> 00:36:01,870
We allowed the traitor
to contact you.

614
00:36:01,870 --> 00:36:04,830
Force opening of traitor.

615
00:36:04,830 --> 00:36:06,630
DOCTOR YELLS

616
00:36:11,670 --> 00:36:13,390
SNARLING

617
00:36:13,390 --> 00:36:16,030
DALEK COMMANDER:
Exterminate the traitor.

618
00:36:16,030 --> 00:36:17,550
DALEKS: Exterminate!

619
00:36:21,150 --> 00:36:23,390
Enter the casing, Doctor.

620
00:36:25,590 --> 00:36:26,630
No!

621
00:36:26,630 --> 00:36:28,110
Obey! Obey!

622
00:36:28,110 --> 00:36:30,270
Or be exterminated!

623
00:36:30,270 --> 00:36:32,910
DOCTOR YELLS

624
00:36:32,910 --> 00:36:34,590
DALEK COMMANDER:
Mission successful.

625
00:36:34,590 --> 00:36:36,910
The Doctor is a prisoner
of the Daleks.

626
00:36:36,910 --> 00:36:39,950
Activate spatiotemporal shift!

627
00:36:48,070 --> 00:36:50,550
I can do this. I can do this.

628
00:36:54,110 --> 00:36:55,630
TARDIS THRUMS

629
00:37:03,350 --> 00:37:05,070
The Doctor's in danger.

630
00:37:05,070 --> 00:37:07,390
There must be a Dalek teleport
trace that we can follow,

631
00:37:07,390 --> 00:37:09,110
that you can lock on to.

632
00:37:09,110 --> 00:37:10,830
And why am I talking to you?

633
00:37:16,950 --> 00:37:18,230
MASTER: Hello, Doctor.

634
00:37:20,390 --> 00:37:23,790
Welcome to the end
of your existence.

635
00:37:23,790 --> 00:37:25,150
Say hello to my friends.

636
00:37:28,510 --> 00:37:30,470
I believe
we're all acquainted...

637
00:37:30,470 --> 00:37:32,950
..right? Do you like the garb?

638
00:37:34,070 --> 00:37:37,550
I love the garb.
Got to dress for the occasion.

639
00:37:38,630 --> 00:37:41,470
I was just thinking...
We could call this...

640
00:37:42,550 --> 00:37:44,750
..the Master's Dalek Plan.

641
00:37:44,750 --> 00:37:46,230
Or the, er...

642
00:37:46,230 --> 00:37:49,670
..Cyber-Dalek Master Plan,
or the Cyber-Master's Dalek Plan?

643
00:37:49,670 --> 00:37:50,710
I can't quite get it.

644
00:37:51,710 --> 00:37:54,190
But in the end
I suppose we'll just call it

645
00:37:54,190 --> 00:37:56,470
the day I killed the Doctor...

646
00:37:58,190 --> 00:37:59,790
..with a little help
from my friends.

647
00:37:59,790 --> 00:38:02,750
SCOFFING: Your friends?
You hate each other.

648
00:38:02,750 --> 00:38:06,150
And the one thing stronger
than their hatred for each other...

649
00:38:07,390 --> 00:38:08,630
..is their hatred for you.

650
00:38:08,630 --> 00:38:12,670
Just took a little handsome genius
to point it out to them.

651
00:38:13,790 --> 00:38:15,590
"What unites us...

652
00:38:16,710 --> 00:38:19,630
"..is stronger
than what divides us."

653
00:38:19,630 --> 00:38:21,710
I mean, that's very you, that,
isn't it?

654
00:38:21,710 --> 00:38:23,990
You love a team, don't you?

655
00:38:23,990 --> 00:38:28,790
Letting every Tom, Dick
and Harriet into your TARDIS...

656
00:38:28,790 --> 00:38:30,470
Well, you have your fam.

657
00:38:30,470 --> 00:38:32,310
Now...

658
00:38:32,310 --> 00:38:33,750
..I have mine.

659
00:38:36,310 --> 00:38:37,990
So everything else was a diversion?

660
00:38:37,990 --> 00:38:39,030
No.

661
00:38:39,030 --> 00:38:40,270
No. No!

662
00:38:40,270 --> 00:38:41,830
Not a diversion.

663
00:38:41,830 --> 00:38:43,230
Very important!

664
00:38:43,230 --> 00:38:44,750
Three-phase plan.

665
00:38:46,350 --> 00:38:47,590
You'll see.

666
00:38:47,590 --> 00:38:48,990
Except you won't.

667
00:38:48,990 --> 00:38:50,230
MASTER LAUGHS

668
00:38:50,230 --> 00:38:53,030
But rest assured,
without you to defend it,

669
00:38:53,030 --> 00:38:55,310
Earth will fall very, very fast.

670
00:38:57,390 --> 00:38:58,990
I did warn you, Doctor.

671
00:39:10,790 --> 00:39:13,150
I'm going old-school, Doctor.

672
00:39:13,150 --> 00:39:15,950
A tribute to our elders.

673
00:39:15,950 --> 00:39:18,750
Do you remember the ultimate
sanction for breaking our laws?

674
00:39:22,310 --> 00:39:25,070
WHISPERS: Forced regeneration.

675
00:39:26,270 --> 00:39:29,110
They even did it to you once,
didn't they?

676
00:39:29,110 --> 00:39:30,790
Well, maybe more than once.
Who knows?

677
00:39:30,790 --> 00:39:31,830
Not you.

678
00:39:31,830 --> 00:39:33,470
You don't have the technology.

679
00:39:33,470 --> 00:39:34,550
I do.

680
00:39:35,590 --> 00:39:37,750
I do.

681
00:39:37,750 --> 00:39:39,070
I do!

682
00:39:39,070 --> 00:39:40,790
MASTER GIGGLES

683
00:39:40,790 --> 00:39:45,030
When I ransacked Gallifrey,
I took everything.

684
00:39:45,030 --> 00:39:47,230
But where would he get the power?

685
00:39:47,230 --> 00:39:51,830
If only I had a planet built
for this purpose.

686
00:39:51,830 --> 00:39:55,430
No, wait, wait. I do!

687
00:39:55,430 --> 00:39:57,070
MASTER LAUGHS MANIACALLY

688
00:39:57,070 --> 00:39:58,670
You did get that, right?

689
00:39:58,670 --> 00:40:00,390
A conversion planet.

690
00:40:01,510 --> 00:40:04,470
Except it doesn't only convert
organic to Cyber.

691
00:40:04,470 --> 00:40:07,070
I brought it here to help
another conversion altogether.

692
00:40:11,510 --> 00:40:14,350
MUSIC: Rasputin by Boney M

693
00:40:18,750 --> 00:40:22,230
# There lived a certain man
in Russia long ago

694
00:40:22,230 --> 00:40:26,030
# He was big and strong
In his eyes a flaming glow

695
00:40:26,030 --> 00:40:29,830
# Most people looked at him
with terror and with fear... #

696
00:40:29,830 --> 00:40:32,270
VINDER: OK, Doctor.
This is my last

697
00:40:32,270 --> 00:40:35,550
roll of the dice. I've been
carrying this around with me

698
00:40:35,550 --> 00:40:36,950
since you gave it to me.

699
00:40:36,950 --> 00:40:41,270
# ..like a preacher
Full of ecstasy and fire

700
00:40:41,270 --> 00:40:44,270
# But he also... #
You need my help?

701
00:40:44,270 --> 00:40:46,790
I could certainly do with yours.

702
00:40:46,790 --> 00:40:48,830
But I'm not holding out much hope.

703
00:40:48,830 --> 00:40:53,950
# Ra-Ra-Rasputin
Lover of the Russian queen

704
00:40:53,950 --> 00:40:56,950
# There was a cat
that really was gone

705
00:40:56,950 --> 00:41:00,950
# Ra-Ra-Rasputin
Russia's greatest love machine

706
00:41:00,950 --> 00:41:05,310
# It was a shame
how he carried on... #

707
00:41:09,150 --> 00:41:10,830
Let's get you out of there.

708
00:41:16,390 --> 00:41:18,150
This is Inston-Vee Vinder
saying,

709
00:41:18,150 --> 00:41:20,870
if you need my help... Vinder!
..I could certainly do with yours.

710
00:41:20,870 --> 00:41:22,150
MASTER: Hello, TARDIS.

711
00:41:24,070 --> 00:41:25,830
Receiving this loud and clear?

712
00:41:25,830 --> 00:41:27,510
Say goodbye, Yaz.

713
00:41:27,510 --> 00:41:29,830
TARDIS, lock on to his signal.

714
00:41:39,630 --> 00:41:41,910
Forced regeneration, Doctor.

715
00:41:43,710 --> 00:41:45,150
To force you...

716
00:41:46,230 --> 00:41:48,590
..to regenerate...

717
00:41:48,590 --> 00:41:50,790
..into me. Oh, no!

718
00:41:51,990 --> 00:41:53,230
You wouldn't.

719
00:42:04,550 --> 00:42:06,590
MASTER YELLS

720
00:42:06,590 --> 00:42:07,910
Yaz!

721
00:42:11,070 --> 00:42:13,470
MASTER ROARS

722
00:42:23,910 --> 00:42:26,110
RAGGED BREATHING

723
00:42:32,110 --> 00:42:33,510
MASTER GROANS

724
00:42:37,710 --> 00:42:39,350
WHISPERS: It worked.

725
00:42:48,070 --> 00:42:50,230
MASTER GROANS WITH TRIUMPH

726
00:42:54,510 --> 00:42:55,950
I...

727
00:42:57,790 --> 00:42:59,350
..am...

728
00:43:02,630 --> 00:43:04,150
..the Doctor.

729
00:43:06,550 --> 00:43:07,990
TARDIS THRUMS

730
00:43:22,030 --> 00:43:23,830
Oh, hello...

731
00:43:23,830 --> 00:43:25,670
..Yasmin Khan.

732
00:43:28,190 --> 00:43:29,710
Where's the Doctor?

733
00:43:29,710 --> 00:43:30,790
MASTER LAUGHS

734
00:43:32,190 --> 00:43:34,470
MY Doctor.

735
00:43:34,470 --> 00:43:35,870
Gone.

736
00:43:38,670 --> 00:43:39,870
Really gone.

737
00:43:40,990 --> 00:43:42,150
Forever gone.

738
00:43:46,550 --> 00:43:48,350
Don't...don't worry.

739
00:43:48,350 --> 00:43:49,710
You'll get used to me.

740
00:43:51,070 --> 00:43:52,590
Everyone will.

741
00:43:56,910 --> 00:44:00,550
I still need a companion
to ask and...

742
00:44:00,550 --> 00:44:02,470
..bask in my brilliance.

743
00:44:04,350 --> 00:44:06,230
Come on, Yaz.

744
00:44:06,230 --> 00:44:08,590
Let's go on an adventure!

745
00:44:11,750 --> 00:44:13,230
Don't make me ask twice.

746
00:44:14,590 --> 00:44:16,710
I'd hate to have
to bring you down to size.

747
00:44:18,830 --> 00:44:20,870
TEGAN: We only just got here!
They're all over

748
00:44:20,870 --> 00:44:23,310
the lower floors!
I have to lock down the building.

749
00:44:23,310 --> 00:44:25,230
I can't risk them
getting into the world.

750
00:44:25,230 --> 00:44:27,470
You both need to leave. How?

751
00:44:27,470 --> 00:44:28,950
You have these panels
in every room.

752
00:44:28,950 --> 00:44:32,030
Automated landing parachutes.

753
00:44:32,030 --> 00:44:34,030
If you can't go down,
you've got to go up.

754
00:44:34,030 --> 00:44:35,750
Off the roof?

755
00:44:35,750 --> 00:44:38,630
You're kidding. I stashed
some of my stuff in here earlier.

756
00:44:38,630 --> 00:44:40,830
Hope you don't mind.

757
00:44:40,830 --> 00:44:42,150
Very '80s.

758
00:44:42,150 --> 00:44:43,830
Thanks. Come on, Tegan.

759
00:44:43,830 --> 00:44:45,670
I'll hold the lockdown
till you're clear.

760
00:44:45,670 --> 00:44:48,350
You carry that bat with you
all the time?

761
00:44:48,350 --> 00:44:49,710
Beyonce copied all my moves.

762
00:44:56,590 --> 00:44:58,070
Come on, Yaz!

763
00:44:58,070 --> 00:45:00,110
Let's save a civilisation!

764
00:45:00,110 --> 00:45:01,590
Let's correct history!

765
00:45:01,590 --> 00:45:03,150
Rescue a sick animal!

766
00:45:04,470 --> 00:45:05,590
These yours?

767
00:45:05,590 --> 00:45:07,550
Oh, bless.

768
00:45:07,550 --> 00:45:09,150
Ow!

769
00:45:09,150 --> 00:45:10,870
What was that?!

770
00:45:10,870 --> 00:45:12,710
Some sort of dirty protest?

771
00:45:12,710 --> 00:45:15,710
Unless you want to be consigned
down a black hole for eternity,

772
00:45:15,710 --> 00:45:17,110
you'd better behave!

773
00:45:17,110 --> 00:45:19,110
I am the Doctor,

774
00:45:19,110 --> 00:45:20,710
and you will obey me.

775
00:45:21,710 --> 00:45:22,990
MASTER BURPS

776
00:45:25,470 --> 00:45:26,550
MASTER GRUNTS

777
00:45:26,550 --> 00:45:28,030
Change back.

778
00:45:28,030 --> 00:45:29,430
Can't be done.

779
00:45:33,310 --> 00:45:35,830
I know you're worried about
what I'm going to do.

780
00:45:35,830 --> 00:45:37,270
It's simple.

781
00:45:37,270 --> 00:45:39,430
The Earth will become
a foundry for Daleks

782
00:45:39,430 --> 00:45:43,230
and Cyber production,
hence the work in the volcano,

783
00:45:43,230 --> 00:45:45,790
while I tarnish the name
of the Doctor.

784
00:45:45,790 --> 00:45:47,990
I'm going to make the Doctor
a byword

785
00:45:47,990 --> 00:45:50,230
for fear, pain and destruction,

786
00:45:50,230 --> 00:45:51,950
so when people hear that name
in future,

787
00:45:51,950 --> 00:45:53,350
they quake in fear. If you think

788
00:45:53,350 --> 00:45:55,910
I am going to let you...!
I am the Doctor now!

789
00:45:55,910 --> 00:45:57,750
I am the Doctor!

790
00:46:01,350 --> 00:46:04,350
MASTER GROANS

791
00:46:04,350 --> 00:46:06,470
You should have shot me
when you had the chance.

792
00:46:08,110 --> 00:46:09,430
I need clothes.

793
00:46:09,430 --> 00:46:12,470
Try to escape,
or touch anything,

794
00:46:12,470 --> 00:46:13,950
and I'll kill you.

795
00:46:18,310 --> 00:46:20,070
Out here!

796
00:46:23,470 --> 00:46:24,870
What are you doing?

797
00:46:26,150 --> 00:46:27,470
We can do this.

798
00:46:27,470 --> 00:46:30,390
I brought them in - the Cybermen.
It's my mistake.

799
00:46:30,390 --> 00:46:32,670
You go, find the Doctor.

800
00:46:32,670 --> 00:46:33,910
I need to help Kate.

801
00:46:34,910 --> 00:46:36,430
Tegan!

802
00:46:45,910 --> 00:46:48,750
MASTER: Oh, lovely.

803
00:46:48,750 --> 00:46:52,230
Gold star and a sticker.

804
00:46:52,230 --> 00:46:56,030
That's how you stop two sides
warring, Yaz.

805
00:46:56,030 --> 00:46:58,150
Destroy them both.

806
00:47:00,990 --> 00:47:02,310
Oh, hello.

807
00:47:02,310 --> 00:47:06,510
I have a message
for all your remaining news viewers.

808
00:47:08,350 --> 00:47:10,150
I am the Doctor.

809
00:47:10,150 --> 00:47:12,150
And I caused this.

810
00:47:19,870 --> 00:47:21,190
See?

811
00:47:21,190 --> 00:47:23,710
No-one to stop me now.

812
00:47:26,350 --> 00:47:27,670
No!

813
00:47:29,150 --> 00:47:31,070
TARDIS THRUMS

814
00:47:34,630 --> 00:47:36,830
I'll wait.

815
00:47:36,830 --> 00:47:38,550
You'll be back.

816
00:47:40,270 --> 00:47:43,510
And I have...all the time.

817
00:47:51,550 --> 00:47:54,910
MUSIC: Skye Boat Song

818
00:48:29,710 --> 00:48:30,830
Well!

819
00:48:30,830 --> 00:48:35,270
You're obviously one
of the more determined of us.

820
00:48:36,270 --> 00:48:37,590
I'm sorry?

821
00:48:37,590 --> 00:48:39,670
You refuse to pass through.

822
00:48:40,830 --> 00:48:43,550
Quite the strength
of character,

823
00:48:43,550 --> 00:48:46,110
this incarnation, mm?

824
00:48:46,110 --> 00:48:51,350
The question is, what are
we going to do about it?

825
00:48:51,350 --> 00:48:52,910
Do about what?

826
00:48:52,910 --> 00:48:54,710
Our predicament!

827
00:48:54,710 --> 00:48:56,510
This is supposed to be
handed over.

828
00:48:56,510 --> 00:48:58,630
You can't ruin it for the next one.

829
00:49:00,030 --> 00:49:02,270
And you were doing so well.

830
00:49:02,270 --> 00:49:03,910
Where am I, exactly?

831
00:49:03,910 --> 00:49:05,470
Because the last thing I remember

832
00:49:05,470 --> 00:49:06,950
is being forced to regenerate.

833
00:49:06,950 --> 00:49:08,630
That's why we're here.

834
00:49:08,630 --> 00:49:11,390
To stop you moving
any further through.

835
00:49:11,390 --> 00:49:13,110
You are not finished.

836
00:49:13,110 --> 00:49:15,510
We are not finished.

837
00:49:15,510 --> 00:49:16,710
"We" being...?

838
00:49:16,710 --> 00:49:18,350
Vestiges of your consciousness.

839
00:49:18,350 --> 00:49:20,030
Fragments of yourself.

840
00:49:20,030 --> 00:49:21,350
From the past.

841
00:49:22,750 --> 00:49:24,470
Guardians of the Edge.

842
00:49:24,470 --> 00:49:26,030
Sorry, why are you not wearing...?

843
00:49:27,190 --> 00:49:28,710
I don't do robes.

844
00:49:28,710 --> 00:49:31,150
There's always one.
Has to be different.

845
00:49:31,150 --> 00:49:33,430
I am a manifestation
of our consciousness.

846
00:49:33,430 --> 00:49:35,190
I can wear what I like.

847
00:49:35,190 --> 00:49:37,190
Could we just focus on this,
whatever this is?

848
00:49:37,190 --> 00:49:39,390
You said Guardians of the Edge.
The edge of what?

849
00:49:41,990 --> 00:49:43,430
DOCTOR GASPS

850
00:49:48,350 --> 00:49:50,070
Existence.

851
00:49:50,070 --> 00:49:53,910
It's symbolic, obviously.
Consciousness will do that.

852
00:49:53,910 --> 00:49:57,350
But this is the place
you pass through

853
00:49:57,350 --> 00:50:00,590
during the process of regeneration.

854
00:50:00,590 --> 00:50:04,190
Go past here, there's no way back.

855
00:50:05,190 --> 00:50:07,950
But time's running out!

856
00:50:07,950 --> 00:50:11,590
We can't let the Master
permanently hijack our existence.

857
00:50:11,590 --> 00:50:13,550
Yes.

858
00:50:13,550 --> 00:50:15,630
Very aware of that.

859
00:50:15,630 --> 00:50:16,830
But I was thinking,

860
00:50:16,830 --> 00:50:20,070
in the immediate aftermath
of regeneration, the body's weak,

861
00:50:20,070 --> 00:50:22,350
unstable while it re-forms.
Very good.

862
00:50:22,350 --> 00:50:25,430
Even more so
with a forced regeneration.

863
00:50:25,430 --> 00:50:28,190
So until it's settled,
he may be vulnerable.

864
00:50:28,190 --> 00:50:32,750
We need help from the outside,
which is easier said than done.

865
00:50:32,750 --> 00:50:36,670
Unless one of us, or all of us,
were really clever.

866
00:50:36,670 --> 00:50:39,270
I mean, this is why
you manifested here!

867
00:50:39,270 --> 00:50:42,750
To remind me there's always a way.

868
00:50:42,750 --> 00:50:44,590
Things always work out!

869
00:50:44,590 --> 00:50:46,470
Right?

870
00:50:47,750 --> 00:50:49,230
Hello?

871
00:50:54,110 --> 00:50:55,590
Come on.
I need to get back to UNIT.

872
00:50:55,590 --> 00:50:57,910
If I can work with the others
to get the Doctor back... Hi!

873
00:50:57,910 --> 00:50:59,270
YAZ SQUEALS

874
00:50:59,270 --> 00:51:01,070
If you're seeing this, I'm dead.

875
00:51:01,070 --> 00:51:02,390
What?

876
00:51:02,390 --> 00:51:04,790
Is that a bad way to start?
Bit overdramatic?

877
00:51:04,790 --> 00:51:05,830
How's it looking?

878
00:51:05,830 --> 00:51:08,830
I have been working on this
literally for ever.

879
00:51:08,830 --> 00:51:10,670
It should adapt and respond to

880
00:51:10,670 --> 00:51:12,870
its environment and whoever
it's interacting with.

881
00:51:12,870 --> 00:51:15,230
It's an interactive AI holo-me!

882
00:51:15,230 --> 00:51:18,150
Built from data of my behaviour
across thousands of years.

883
00:51:18,150 --> 00:51:19,910
And it should only activate

884
00:51:19,910 --> 00:51:22,110
under the gravest circumstances.

885
00:51:22,110 --> 00:51:23,750
Like if I'm no longer around.

886
00:51:23,750 --> 00:51:26,830
Now, that would be disastrous.
But I will have very subtly

887
00:51:26,830 --> 00:51:29,910
inserted a sonically triggered
nano-implant under your skin

888
00:51:29,910 --> 00:51:31,790
and passed it off
as static electricity.

889
00:51:31,790 --> 00:51:33,350
Ow! Oh!

890
00:51:33,350 --> 00:51:35,710
If I remember to do that.
I must remember to do that.

891
00:51:35,710 --> 00:51:37,350
You could have told us
you'd done that.

892
00:51:37,350 --> 00:51:38,990
Whoa! The emotional receptors
on the AI

893
00:51:38,990 --> 00:51:40,070
are a bit oversensitive.

894
00:51:40,070 --> 00:51:41,630
Apparently, you're annoyed with me?

895
00:51:41,630 --> 00:51:43,870
Apparently, I should apologise
for something?

896
00:51:43,870 --> 00:51:45,150
I've got a plan.

897
00:51:45,150 --> 00:51:46,950
Tell me if I'm doing this right.

898
00:51:48,630 --> 00:51:51,070
TARDIS THRUMS

899
00:51:55,550 --> 00:51:57,710
Who said miracles don't happen?

900
00:52:01,110 --> 00:52:02,270
The Doctor's gone?

901
00:52:02,270 --> 00:52:04,990
Worse than gone.
And we're the only ones to help her.

902
00:52:04,990 --> 00:52:06,390
Could you go through it again,

903
00:52:06,390 --> 00:52:09,390
but slowly? No! We're on our way
to our next pick-up. I hope.

904
00:52:09,390 --> 00:52:11,950
Doctor, I need information.

905
00:52:11,950 --> 00:52:13,590
Hiya.

906
00:52:13,590 --> 00:52:15,110
Hi, Vinder! How's she doing that?

907
00:52:15,110 --> 00:52:17,110
Sh! Doctor...

908
00:52:17,110 --> 00:52:19,510
How do you reverse
a forced regeneration?

909
00:52:19,510 --> 00:52:21,190
No, no, no, no.

910
00:52:21,190 --> 00:52:24,710
Forced regeneration isn't something
you ever want to be dealing with.

911
00:52:27,550 --> 00:52:29,510
Is that what's happened to me?

912
00:52:31,270 --> 00:52:33,310
It's a hologram.

913
00:52:33,310 --> 00:52:35,430
Can't hurt the feelings
of a hologram.

914
00:52:38,390 --> 00:52:39,790
Yeah.

915
00:52:40,870 --> 00:52:43,030
How do we get real you back?

916
00:52:43,030 --> 00:52:44,390
Real you.

917
00:52:44,390 --> 00:52:46,310
No. Impossible.

918
00:52:46,310 --> 00:52:47,390
Unless...

919
00:52:47,390 --> 00:52:48,870
No.

920
00:52:48,870 --> 00:52:51,070
Calibrating. I'm thinking.

921
00:52:51,070 --> 00:52:52,630
What...what was that?

922
00:52:52,630 --> 00:52:55,230
Other interfaces, other me's.

923
00:52:55,230 --> 00:52:57,190
Sorry,
I'm processing the information.

924
00:52:57,190 --> 00:52:59,150
Only one chance.

925
00:52:59,150 --> 00:53:02,030
I've seen it
in extreme circumstances.

926
00:53:02,030 --> 00:53:03,990
It's incredibly dangerous.

927
00:53:05,590 --> 00:53:07,150
Anything could happen.

928
00:53:08,350 --> 00:53:10,110
Are these extreme circumstances?

929
00:53:17,070 --> 00:53:19,910
CYBERMAN: Conversion pod
established.

930
00:53:19,910 --> 00:53:21,830
ASHAD: Let the conversions begin.

931
00:53:21,830 --> 00:53:26,670
Their army shall become ours.

932
00:53:26,670 --> 00:53:28,670
HE GROANS

933
00:53:32,110 --> 00:53:33,710
What are you doing?
You're supposed to

934
00:53:33,710 --> 00:53:36,830
be getting out of here.
Yeah, well, I didn't.

935
00:53:36,830 --> 00:53:38,670
I don't have time to factor you in!

936
00:53:38,670 --> 00:53:42,750
I have spent the past 30 years
living like a nomad.

937
00:53:42,750 --> 00:53:45,710
I have done land mines, coups,

938
00:53:45,710 --> 00:53:47,350
I have been hijacked,

939
00:53:47,350 --> 00:53:50,350
and I've nearly drowned
trying to help people.

940
00:53:50,350 --> 00:53:51,990
I've seen off two husbands,

941
00:53:51,990 --> 00:53:54,710
and somewhere out there
is an adopted son

942
00:53:54,710 --> 00:53:57,350
who hasn't called me
for six weeks.

943
00:53:57,350 --> 00:53:59,350
And if that's not enough,

944
00:53:59,350 --> 00:54:02,190
I was an air hostess
in the early '80s,

945
00:54:02,190 --> 00:54:04,750
and, trust me, compared to that,

946
00:54:04,750 --> 00:54:08,190
a building full of Cybermen
is nothing.

947
00:54:08,190 --> 00:54:10,510
Now, what's the plan?

948
00:54:11,870 --> 00:54:14,510
Containment
and structural termination.

949
00:54:15,830 --> 00:54:17,550
They've taken out all the systems,

950
00:54:17,550 --> 00:54:20,710
but in the basement
there's a manual activation override

951
00:54:20,710 --> 00:54:22,390
for the structural
termination system.

952
00:54:22,390 --> 00:54:26,430
It'll level the building,
leave everything inside entombed.

953
00:54:28,510 --> 00:54:29,790
You said basement.

954
00:54:29,790 --> 00:54:32,390
We're at the top of the building,
with Cybermen in between.

955
00:54:32,390 --> 00:54:34,270
There is a way out. It's not pretty.

956
00:54:34,270 --> 00:54:37,070
But if you can get down there,
I'll distract the Cybermen.

957
00:54:37,070 --> 00:54:38,630
How are you going to do that?

958
00:54:40,070 --> 00:54:42,470
SCREAMING

959
00:54:45,310 --> 00:54:46,990
KATE: Attention, Cybermen.

960
00:54:46,990 --> 00:54:49,550
I am the commanding officer
of this facility

961
00:54:49,550 --> 00:54:51,670
and I have an offer for you...

962
00:54:52,710 --> 00:54:54,470
..if you can find me, that is.

963
00:54:56,910 --> 00:54:58,270
With me!

964
00:54:58,270 --> 00:54:59,670
SCREAMING

965
00:55:08,310 --> 00:55:10,390
Er...OK.

966
00:55:10,390 --> 00:55:11,670
That's high.

967
00:55:15,070 --> 00:55:16,270
Oh, come on.

968
00:55:16,270 --> 00:55:17,990
This used to be easy.

969
00:55:19,550 --> 00:55:21,310
I used to be good with heights.

970
00:55:23,270 --> 00:55:24,550
Just do it.

971
00:55:26,070 --> 00:55:27,310
Just step off.

972
00:55:31,950 --> 00:55:33,230
ACE YELLS

973
00:55:42,830 --> 00:55:45,310
ACE YELLS

974
00:55:45,310 --> 00:55:47,270
How do you brake?!

975
00:55:47,270 --> 00:55:48,630
What?!

976
00:55:48,630 --> 00:55:49,950
ACE YELLS

977
00:56:00,350 --> 00:56:02,990
Hi. Did you do that?

978
00:56:02,990 --> 00:56:05,150
Can you fly the TARDIS?
Does she let you?

979
00:56:05,150 --> 00:56:06,910
I never got to fly the TARDIS.

980
00:56:06,910 --> 00:56:09,230
Whoa. Nice vibe.
Where's the Doctor? Hi.

981
00:56:09,230 --> 00:56:11,030
I'm Ace. Inston-Vee Vinder.

982
00:56:11,030 --> 00:56:12,430
Ace, how would you feel

983
00:56:12,430 --> 00:56:14,590
about me dropping you
under a Bolivian volcano

984
00:56:14,590 --> 00:56:17,030
so you can stop the Daleks from
flooding the world with lava?

985
00:56:17,030 --> 00:56:18,790
BAT SCRAPES

986
00:56:17,030 --> 00:56:18,790
Wicked.

987
00:56:18,790 --> 00:56:21,950
Vinder, our mission is
even more dangerous than that.

988
00:56:24,350 --> 00:56:26,550
TARDIS THRUMS

989
00:56:34,590 --> 00:56:35,750
Better.

990
00:56:35,750 --> 00:56:37,590
TARDIS DOOR SHUTS

991
00:56:42,030 --> 00:56:43,150
I'm sorry.

992
00:56:44,430 --> 00:56:45,790
Are you?

993
00:56:46,990 --> 00:56:48,750
Truly?

994
00:56:48,750 --> 00:56:50,430
Came back, didn't I?

995
00:56:55,830 --> 00:56:57,990
We could have fun, you know?

996
00:56:59,230 --> 00:57:00,510
I am fun.

997
00:57:01,670 --> 00:57:04,030
Different type of fun, but fun.

998
00:57:05,870 --> 00:57:07,390
We could travel.

999
00:57:10,070 --> 00:57:11,230
You'll see.

1000
00:57:18,070 --> 00:57:21,470
TARDIS THRUMS

1001
00:57:28,190 --> 00:57:30,790
HOLO-DOCTOR: Good hiding place.
TEGAN GASPS

1002
00:57:31,830 --> 00:57:34,870
Great. Now I'm hallucinating.

1003
00:57:36,270 --> 00:57:37,630
What...? What are...?

1004
00:57:40,030 --> 00:57:42,910
You're affecting the interface
of your hologram implant!

1005
00:57:42,910 --> 00:57:45,510
It's reacting
to your emotional memory.

1006
00:57:45,510 --> 00:57:47,230
I should have accounted for that.

1007
00:57:47,230 --> 00:57:49,710
You sort of look like
you used to, but...

1008
00:57:49,710 --> 00:57:51,070
..not quite.

1009
00:57:52,190 --> 00:57:53,750
I could say the same to you.

1010
00:57:53,750 --> 00:57:55,350
Surprised you remember.

1011
00:57:55,350 --> 00:57:58,390
You think you left and I never
thought of you again.

1012
00:57:59,430 --> 00:58:02,190
I never forget any of you.

1013
00:58:02,190 --> 00:58:04,190
I remember everything.

1014
00:58:04,190 --> 00:58:05,350
Yeah?

1015
00:58:05,350 --> 00:58:08,150
Well, what am I thinking,
seeing all these Cybermen?

1016
00:58:08,150 --> 00:58:10,190
DISTANT MARCHING

1017
00:58:08,150 --> 00:58:10,190
Adric.

1018
00:58:12,590 --> 00:58:14,710
Now... Brave heart.

1019
00:58:16,030 --> 00:58:17,310
What?

1020
00:58:17,310 --> 00:58:19,430
I missed you.

1021
00:58:20,430 --> 00:58:22,030
Missed you too.

1022
00:58:22,030 --> 00:58:25,070
Now, please, don't get killed. Go!

1023
00:58:32,750 --> 00:58:34,310
TEGAN GRUNTS

1024
00:58:46,030 --> 00:58:49,190
DALEK: Tectonic plate depth
achieved.

1025
00:58:51,630 --> 00:58:56,430
Progress plan
to next phase of activation.

1026
00:58:56,430 --> 00:58:57,790
I think I might have

1027
00:58:57,790 --> 00:59:01,030
slightly overestimated myself here,
Professor.

1028
00:59:01,030 --> 00:59:05,230
Although...
I have souped up the Nitro 9.

1029
00:59:05,230 --> 00:59:07,070
Nitro 999!

1030
00:59:07,070 --> 00:59:09,470
Just what we need. Good work, Ace.

1031
00:59:09,470 --> 00:59:12,950
How are you doing that?
In case you need help, but it
looks like you're doing fine.

1032
00:59:12,950 --> 00:59:15,870
So it's fine for me to blow
stuff up when you decide?

1033
00:59:15,870 --> 00:59:17,670
Nothing's changed.

1034
00:59:18,830 --> 00:59:21,150
It's never fine to blow stuff up.

1035
00:59:22,430 --> 00:59:25,910
Sometimes, sadly,
it's the only solution.

1036
00:59:25,910 --> 00:59:28,310
But only after fair warning.

1037
00:59:29,630 --> 00:59:31,030
Now it's getting freaky.

1038
00:59:31,030 --> 00:59:35,230
I was only ever trying
to teach you good habits, Ace.

1039
00:59:36,470 --> 00:59:38,110
Obviously, I failed.

1040
00:59:38,110 --> 00:59:40,230
You never failed me, Professor.

1041
00:59:40,230 --> 00:59:43,030
You made me the person I am today.

1042
00:59:47,230 --> 00:59:48,790
I'm sorry we fell out.

1043
00:59:49,950 --> 00:59:51,750
I'm sorry I judged you.

1044
00:59:52,990 --> 00:59:55,990
I didn't understand
the burden you carried.

1045
00:59:55,990 --> 00:59:59,430
All children leave home
sooner or later.

1046
00:59:59,430 --> 01:00:03,110
The joy is to watch them fly.

1047
01:00:04,830 --> 01:00:07,510
So...we're good?

1048
01:00:07,510 --> 01:00:09,830
Oh, we're more than good.

1049
01:00:09,830 --> 01:00:11,630
We're ace!

1050
01:00:15,950 --> 01:00:18,350
Now, let's get that Nitro 999 going.

1051
01:00:18,350 --> 01:00:21,510
DALEK 1: Power levels
now increasing.

1052
01:00:21,510 --> 01:00:24,990
DALEK 2: Prepare to engage
circuit four.

1053
01:00:24,990 --> 01:00:28,230
DALEK 3: All sectors
now engaging full power.

1054
01:00:28,230 --> 01:00:30,310
ACE SHOUTS, GRAHAM YELPS

1055
01:00:30,310 --> 01:00:32,190
Oh, you, er...

1056
01:00:32,190 --> 01:00:33,550
Easy, love.

1057
01:00:33,550 --> 01:00:35,870
Arnold Palmer...son.

1058
01:00:35,870 --> 01:00:37,710
Volcano inspector.

1059
01:00:37,710 --> 01:00:39,470
"Graham, friend of the Doctor." Oh!

1060
01:00:39,470 --> 01:00:42,150
"Former bus driver, worried
about the amount of Daleks

1061
01:00:42,150 --> 01:00:44,510
"in here and what he's going
to do about it."

1062
01:00:44,510 --> 01:00:46,390
I can't get the hang of this.

1063
01:00:46,390 --> 01:00:51,150
Listen, those metal things -
they are from outer space,

1064
01:00:51,150 --> 01:00:53,750
and they seem to be drilling
to disrupt the tectonic plates.

1065
01:00:53,750 --> 01:00:56,710
We've got to get rid of them
a bit sharpish. I know.

1066
01:00:56,710 --> 01:00:58,670
Want to see how I dealt
with them in 1963?

1067
01:00:58,670 --> 01:01:00,870
196...? How old are you?

1068
01:01:00,870 --> 01:01:02,350
Excuse me!

1069
01:01:02,350 --> 01:01:05,350
A gentleman never asks that,
and never on the first date.

1070
01:01:05,350 --> 01:01:07,390
I'm Ace.

1071
01:01:07,390 --> 01:01:09,430
Yes, you are.

1072
01:01:11,550 --> 01:01:14,630
CYBERMAN: Human
structural defences removed.

1073
01:01:14,630 --> 01:01:17,590
UNIT commander detected
in this area.

1074
01:01:17,590 --> 01:01:18,830
KATE: That's far enough.

1075
01:01:18,830 --> 01:01:21,310
Any further,
and that laser shield

1076
01:01:21,310 --> 01:01:22,910
will shred at least some of you.

1077
01:01:22,910 --> 01:01:24,590
You should know that reinforcements

1078
01:01:24,590 --> 01:01:27,270
are already on the way
from all around the world.

1079
01:01:27,270 --> 01:01:28,310
ASHAD: Let them come.

1080
01:01:29,550 --> 01:01:32,750
They will be recruits
for the new Cyber Army.

1081
01:01:32,750 --> 01:01:36,390
We will spread from this building
in fire and glory

1082
01:01:36,390 --> 01:01:38,190
to conquer humanity.

1083
01:01:38,190 --> 01:01:41,350
You underestimate us.
I understand you.

1084
01:01:41,350 --> 01:01:45,950
I was like you - weak and feeble.

1085
01:01:47,590 --> 01:01:49,230
Actually, I'm neither.

1086
01:01:55,270 --> 01:01:57,310
I have knowledge of this planet...

1087
01:01:58,390 --> 01:02:01,190
..of its security infrastructure,
of its leaders.

1088
01:02:01,190 --> 01:02:03,030
You have no reason to offer this.

1089
01:02:03,030 --> 01:02:05,350
Release all the soldiers you hold.

1090
01:02:06,590 --> 01:02:08,390
Save them from conversion.

1091
01:02:08,390 --> 01:02:09,710
Let them go...

1092
01:02:10,830 --> 01:02:12,510
..and you can have me.

1093
01:02:14,110 --> 01:02:16,470
I'm of greater strategic value.

1094
01:02:23,190 --> 01:02:27,830
You calculate this may earn you time
for reinforcements to arrive.

1095
01:02:28,910 --> 01:02:30,230
You are wrong.

1096
01:02:31,230 --> 01:02:33,510
The Doctor is not coming.

1097
01:02:33,510 --> 01:02:37,030
The Doctor will never
save you again.

1098
01:02:37,030 --> 01:02:39,670
I choose to believe otherwise.

1099
01:02:41,190 --> 01:02:43,350
Your surrender is accepted.

1100
01:02:49,350 --> 01:02:52,470
Your conversion shall begin.

1101
01:03:14,230 --> 01:03:16,350
TEGAN GASPS

1102
01:03:14,230 --> 01:03:16,350
Argh!

1103
01:03:22,830 --> 01:03:24,350
TEGAN GROANS AND STRAINS

1104
01:03:25,470 --> 01:03:27,830
CLANGING

1105
01:03:25,470 --> 01:03:27,830
Rabbits!

1106
01:03:28,950 --> 01:03:31,390
Renegade human in the walls.

1107
01:03:31,390 --> 01:03:33,510
LASER FIRE

1108
01:03:33,510 --> 01:03:35,110
TEGAN SCREAMS

1109
01:03:41,350 --> 01:03:43,190
TEGAN YELLS

1110
01:03:43,190 --> 01:03:47,350
MASTER: Ah, thank you for waiting,
my precious fam.

1111
01:03:49,470 --> 01:03:51,350
And now it's time to kill...

1112
01:03:51,350 --> 01:03:52,670
..everyone.

1113
01:03:58,630 --> 01:04:00,230
Unleash the volcanoes.

1114
01:04:00,230 --> 01:04:03,750
DALEK: Volcanic eruptions
shall commence.

1115
01:04:03,750 --> 01:04:06,470
COMMANDER DALEK:
Disruptor pulse activation.

1116
01:04:06,470 --> 01:04:08,870
Destabilising tectonic plates.

1117
01:04:08,870 --> 01:04:11,430
DALEK 1: Every volcano
on planet Earth

1118
01:04:11,430 --> 01:04:12,830
shall be activated!

1119
01:04:12,830 --> 01:04:15,630
DALEK 2: All humans
shall be exterminated.

1120
01:04:28,430 --> 01:04:30,630
CYBERMASTER: Tectonic
disruption in progress.

1121
01:04:30,630 --> 01:04:32,430
Volcanic eruptions increasing

1122
01:04:32,430 --> 01:04:34,470
across the surface of planet Earth.

1123
01:04:34,470 --> 01:04:35,910
YAZ: You're not the Doctor.

1124
01:04:36,910 --> 01:04:38,510
You'll never be the Doctor.

1125
01:04:41,710 --> 01:04:43,590
On reflection, Yaz,

1126
01:04:43,590 --> 01:04:46,470
I think they make much better
companions than you.

1127
01:04:47,590 --> 01:04:49,310
I think it's time
for your execution.

1128
01:04:49,310 --> 01:04:50,990
Yeah? Well,

1129
01:04:50,990 --> 01:04:54,630
if they're much better than me,
why didn't they spot her come in?

1130
01:04:58,990 --> 01:05:00,790
What's going on? Who are you?

1131
01:05:03,830 --> 01:05:05,190
I'm the Doctor, mate.

1132
01:05:05,190 --> 01:05:06,670
Who the hell are you?

1133
01:05:06,670 --> 01:05:08,510
Shoot her.

1134
01:05:08,510 --> 01:05:10,110
Are you sure
you want to do that, boys?

1135
01:05:10,110 --> 01:05:11,550
Fire!

1136
01:05:18,710 --> 01:05:22,110
So...it was just
the genetic material

1137
01:05:22,110 --> 01:05:23,430
you put into them, was it?

1138
01:05:23,430 --> 01:05:25,950
Maybe you should have
included the brains.

1139
01:05:25,950 --> 01:05:29,470
Next time,
check for signs of a hologram.

1140
01:05:30,550 --> 01:05:32,230
Schoolboy error.

1141
01:05:32,230 --> 01:05:34,830
But then you were
a rubbish schoolboy, too.

1142
01:05:34,830 --> 01:05:36,190
Was this you?

1143
01:05:37,390 --> 01:05:41,270
Out-thought by the Doctor.
Get in the machine.

1144
01:05:41,270 --> 01:05:42,910
Or you'll what?

1145
01:05:42,910 --> 01:05:44,230
VINDER: You heard her.

1146
01:05:44,230 --> 01:05:46,230
Quickly.

1147
01:05:46,230 --> 01:05:47,590
And who are you?

1148
01:05:48,630 --> 01:05:50,150
Did you stow away in my TARDIS?

1149
01:05:50,150 --> 01:05:51,190
It's not your TARDIS.

1150
01:05:51,190 --> 01:05:54,270
If you're a friend
of the Doctor's...

1151
01:05:54,270 --> 01:05:55,790
..you aren't going to use that.

1152
01:05:56,830 --> 01:05:59,070
MASTER GRUNTS

1153
01:05:59,070 --> 01:06:00,430
I'm freelance.

1154
01:06:00,430 --> 01:06:03,110
You going to let him do this
to me, Yaz? Huh?

1155
01:06:03,110 --> 01:06:04,990
To your Doctor?
You're not my Doctor!

1156
01:06:04,990 --> 01:06:07,670
Because you know the greatest
strength my Doctor has?

1157
01:06:07,670 --> 01:06:09,630
She's spent her life
gathering friends.

1158
01:06:09,630 --> 01:06:11,310
She can't help it.

1159
01:06:11,310 --> 01:06:13,150
And she is loved.

1160
01:06:13,150 --> 01:06:15,430
Because she taught us
to never give up,

1161
01:06:15,430 --> 01:06:17,910
even if someone steals
your very existence.

1162
01:06:17,910 --> 01:06:19,430
HIGH-PITCHED WHIR

1163
01:06:19,430 --> 01:06:21,030
They're starting.

1164
01:06:21,030 --> 01:06:23,350
Yaz, over there.

1165
01:06:23,350 --> 01:06:25,430
We've got to harness
their regenerative energy.

1166
01:06:25,430 --> 01:06:28,230
Right, burst of two seconds,
and then link it into that.

1167
01:06:28,230 --> 01:06:31,190
No! This is weird. You were
a tour guide in Gloucester

1168
01:06:31,190 --> 01:06:32,350
the last time I saw you.

1169
01:06:32,350 --> 01:06:34,030
Nice trick to use
a different interface

1170
01:06:34,030 --> 01:06:35,510
to confuse this lot.

1171
01:06:35,510 --> 01:06:36,750
Now!

1172
01:06:43,670 --> 01:06:45,190
No! Will it be enough?

1173
01:06:45,190 --> 01:06:48,390
Hopefully. Enough to reverse.

1174
01:06:50,350 --> 01:06:51,870
MASTER ROARS

1175
01:06:50,350 --> 01:06:51,870
It's happening.

1176
01:06:51,870 --> 01:06:54,030
Is it safe? I hope so.

1177
01:06:56,670 --> 01:06:58,870
I erased you, Doctor.

1178
01:07:00,150 --> 01:07:02,870
Don't let me go back to being me.

1179
01:07:06,750 --> 01:07:08,350
What's happening?

1180
01:07:08,350 --> 01:07:11,230
Concentrate! Reunite.

1181
01:07:11,230 --> 01:07:13,070
Yes. Where there's hope...

1182
01:07:14,230 --> 01:07:16,150
Good luck... Doctor.

1183
01:07:18,310 --> 01:07:19,670
MASTER GROANS

1184
01:07:25,230 --> 01:07:27,910
DOCTOR PANTS

1185
01:07:30,950 --> 01:07:32,190
Hi.

1186
01:07:36,030 --> 01:07:37,350
What did I miss?

1187
01:07:39,390 --> 01:07:41,110
What am I wearing?!

1188
01:07:45,590 --> 01:07:47,830
Forced regeneration.

1189
01:07:47,830 --> 01:07:49,350
Forced degeneration.

1190
01:07:49,350 --> 01:07:50,950
You brought me back!

1191
01:07:50,950 --> 01:07:53,910
Yaz, you saved my life.

1192
01:07:53,910 --> 01:07:55,510
You're welcome.

1193
01:07:58,910 --> 01:08:00,310
Guess that's me done.

1194
01:08:00,310 --> 01:08:04,630
My AI hologram worked.
Oh, I am a genius.

1195
01:08:05,870 --> 01:08:07,430
See you around.

1196
01:08:09,270 --> 01:08:10,830
Vinder, what are you doing here?

1197
01:08:10,830 --> 01:08:12,910
Oh! Whoa, you all right?

1198
01:08:14,110 --> 01:08:15,910
Whole new lease of life.

1199
01:08:15,910 --> 01:08:18,110
If memory serves me...

1200
01:08:18,110 --> 01:08:20,310
..we've got a lot to do. Come on.

1201
01:08:24,470 --> 01:08:27,830
ASHAD: Your soldiers offered
pitiful resistance.

1202
01:08:27,830 --> 01:08:29,830
They shall begin their ascension,

1203
01:08:29,830 --> 01:08:33,030
as you shall now receive yours.

1204
01:08:35,190 --> 01:08:38,910
I bestow upon you
the greatest of gifts.

1205
01:08:40,270 --> 01:08:41,990
Your conversion shall begin.

1206
01:08:44,710 --> 01:08:46,990
KATE: No, no...

1207
01:08:48,550 --> 01:08:49,750
No...

1208
01:08:49,750 --> 01:08:51,750
No, no...

1209
01:08:51,750 --> 01:08:53,310
No, no!

1210
01:08:53,310 --> 01:08:55,790
KATE SCREAMS

1211
01:09:04,070 --> 01:09:07,430
Oh, my God, it's worse
than a cockpit. Extra wrinkle.

1212
01:09:07,430 --> 01:09:09,550
Right, divert that power
into that circuit.

1213
01:09:10,750 --> 01:09:12,990
You're not even here!
I'm everywhere, me.

1214
01:09:12,990 --> 01:09:16,550
I'm using your ocular nerve
to scan, analyse and process.

1215
01:09:16,550 --> 01:09:19,630
The Cyber conversion unit
is powering itself from here,

1216
01:09:19,630 --> 01:09:22,470
but if we change that, then
they'll get a nasty surprise!

1217
01:09:25,870 --> 01:09:27,110
BEEPING

1218
01:09:27,110 --> 01:09:28,470
SMASH, TEGAN YELLS

1219
01:09:28,470 --> 01:09:31,830
CYBERMAN: Human rebel located.
You will be deleted.

1220
01:09:31,830 --> 01:09:33,910
TEGAN SCREAMS

1221
01:09:35,830 --> 01:09:38,430
Human resistance
no longer anticipated.

1222
01:09:41,710 --> 01:09:43,030
KATE SCREAMS

1223
01:09:59,990 --> 01:10:03,510
Daleks are setting off
volcanoes in 2022,

1224
01:10:03,510 --> 01:10:05,670
and here, in 1916,

1225
01:10:05,670 --> 01:10:07,590
there's a big Cyber planet

1226
01:10:07,590 --> 01:10:09,670
which could convert
the whole of Earth.

1227
01:10:09,670 --> 01:10:11,430
There's definitely a fix for both.

1228
01:10:12,830 --> 01:10:14,230
But it's got to be quick.

1229
01:10:15,630 --> 01:10:17,070
Just piecing it all together.

1230
01:10:28,910 --> 01:10:30,750
We used to be friends...

1231
01:10:30,750 --> 01:10:32,270
..him and me.

1232
01:10:36,510 --> 01:10:39,190
So how do we fix
all those problems?

1233
01:10:42,230 --> 01:10:44,070
Have you not figured it out yet?

1234
01:10:44,070 --> 01:10:46,470
Obvious, isn't it? We're going
to need some help, though.

1235
01:10:46,470 --> 01:10:47,550
All hands on deck.

1236
01:10:51,070 --> 01:10:52,670
Oi! Pepper pot!

1237
01:10:55,350 --> 01:10:56,510
Now, Graham!

1238
01:10:56,510 --> 01:10:59,670
DALEK: Vision impaired!
How long are the timers? Run!

1239
01:11:04,030 --> 01:11:06,030
Timer still needs work. Yeah.

1240
01:11:06,030 --> 01:11:07,310
Pack a load of Nitro onto this.

1241
01:11:07,310 --> 01:11:09,350
Right. Should bring it down.

1242
01:11:09,350 --> 01:11:11,430
Well, I hope the timers
last longer on this batch,

1243
01:11:11,430 --> 01:11:13,110
cos the moment
this little lot goes up,

1244
01:11:13,110 --> 01:11:14,830
we've got to get
to the surface fast,

1245
01:11:14,830 --> 01:11:16,390
get past a load of angry Daleks,

1246
01:11:16,390 --> 01:11:18,390
and I'd like to make it
out of here alive.

1247
01:11:18,390 --> 01:11:20,150
Ready? Ready.

1248
01:11:21,830 --> 01:11:23,430
BEEPING

1249
01:11:23,430 --> 01:11:24,670
TARDIS THRUMS

1250
01:11:26,910 --> 01:11:28,630
Graham! Hey, Doc!

1251
01:11:28,630 --> 01:11:31,790
BOTH: How did you get here?
It's about to blow, Professor!

1252
01:11:31,790 --> 01:11:33,710
DALEK: Sabotage!

1253
01:11:33,710 --> 01:11:35,950
The Doctor is still alive!

1254
01:11:33,710 --> 01:11:35,950
TARDIS THRUMS

1255
01:11:35,950 --> 01:11:37,590
Exterminate!

1256
01:11:48,190 --> 01:11:49,750
BOTH YELL

1257
01:11:49,750 --> 01:11:51,470
BOTH GASP

1258
01:11:54,950 --> 01:11:56,910
I'd only just signed the lease.

1259
01:12:00,550 --> 01:12:01,830
Wow.

1260
01:12:01,830 --> 01:12:03,830
Remind me never to mess
with either of you.

1261
01:12:03,830 --> 01:12:05,470
I thought that was a given!

1262
01:12:05,470 --> 01:12:08,990
And, yes, I would like
to go in the TARDIS.

1263
01:12:10,390 --> 01:12:11,710
Ah.

1264
01:12:11,710 --> 01:12:13,150
Kate?

1265
01:12:14,990 --> 01:12:16,710
SCRABBLING

1266
01:12:19,230 --> 01:12:20,870
MASTER GRUNTS

1267
01:12:29,350 --> 01:12:31,990
TARDIS THRUMS

1268
01:12:31,990 --> 01:12:33,670
OK.

1269
01:12:33,670 --> 01:12:36,350
So now it really is crowded
in here, just how I like it.

1270
01:12:36,350 --> 01:12:38,910
There you go. I'm going to need
every single one of you.

1271
01:12:38,910 --> 01:12:41,150
Stand there.
No, no, no, not that! No?

1272
01:12:41,150 --> 01:12:43,470
There. Yes. Good. OK.

1273
01:12:43,470 --> 01:12:44,910
Everybody OK?

1274
01:12:44,910 --> 01:12:47,510
THEY ALL TALK AT ONCE

1275
01:12:48,470 --> 01:12:50,150
No, sorry. No time.

1276
01:12:50,150 --> 01:12:51,230
Where's Ryan?

1277
01:12:51,230 --> 01:12:53,070
Patagonia. Vinder, is that your ship

1278
01:12:53,070 --> 01:12:55,510
on the surface of this Cyber
planet? Don't speak. No time.

1279
01:12:55,510 --> 01:12:56,790
Come with me.

1280
01:12:56,790 --> 01:12:58,390
Another problem to solve.

1281
01:12:58,390 --> 01:13:01,430
When I say now,
activate everything.

1282
01:13:01,430 --> 01:13:03,070
Chop chop, Vinder.

1283
01:13:03,070 --> 01:13:04,990
She's still not explaining
anything, then?

1284
01:13:04,990 --> 01:13:08,030
How is it bigger on the inside?

1285
01:13:10,390 --> 01:13:12,350
Never happier than
when I'm fixing things.

1286
01:13:13,350 --> 01:13:16,510
What a ship! Stellar engineering.
Proper build.

1287
01:13:16,510 --> 01:13:19,270
HISSING

1288
01:13:16,510 --> 01:13:19,270
Whoo! Bit of wormhole damage.

1289
01:13:19,270 --> 01:13:22,910
Still loads of miles in this,
if you've got an excellent engineer.

1290
01:13:22,910 --> 01:13:24,110
Which I am!

1291
01:13:24,110 --> 01:13:26,350
Repairs complete.
What are you waiting for?

1292
01:13:26,350 --> 01:13:28,750
Get in. Start her up.
You need to be off this planet

1293
01:13:28,750 --> 01:13:30,510
while the wormhole's still there.

1294
01:13:31,630 --> 01:13:34,670
Thank you, Doctor.
Thanks for being there for me.

1295
01:13:36,030 --> 01:13:39,230
How's your family, by the way?
Send them my love.

1296
01:13:39,230 --> 01:13:41,870
Remember, when I say now,
get off the planet's surface.

1297
01:13:41,870 --> 01:13:43,390
Safe travels.

1298
01:13:48,670 --> 01:13:50,550
Everyone still in position?

1299
01:13:50,550 --> 01:13:52,790
Good. I'm in the Master's TARDIS.

1300
01:13:52,790 --> 01:13:54,470
He's clever,
I'll give him that.

1301
01:13:54,470 --> 01:13:58,830
Using a TARDIS to power
the spatiotemporal movement

1302
01:13:58,830 --> 01:14:00,950
of a Cyber conversion planet.

1303
01:14:00,950 --> 01:14:03,230
What a mind, what a TARDIS!
Type 75.

1304
01:14:03,230 --> 01:14:06,390
Bit flashy for my tastes,
but way more powerful than mine.

1305
01:14:06,390 --> 01:14:08,870
But he's pushed his TARDIS
right to the edge,

1306
01:14:08,870 --> 01:14:12,110
burned out half his systems,
marooned himself here. So,

1307
01:14:12,110 --> 01:14:13,470
I'm linking the TARDISes.

1308
01:14:13,470 --> 01:14:15,430
I'm using mine to jump-start his.

1309
01:14:15,430 --> 01:14:18,150
So when I say now,
activate the control I gave you

1310
01:14:18,150 --> 01:14:20,150
and we'll have
a double-powered TARDIS.

1311
01:14:20,150 --> 01:14:22,150
Now.
Go, go, go!

1312
01:14:24,390 --> 01:14:26,990
TARDIS THRUMS

1313
01:14:29,910 --> 01:14:31,590
Ha! She did it!

1314
01:14:31,590 --> 01:14:33,190
Thank you, Doctor!

1315
01:14:36,670 --> 01:14:40,150
Vinder heading home, tick.

1316
01:14:40,150 --> 01:14:42,310
She really doesn't like it!

1317
01:14:42,310 --> 01:14:43,710
Are you sure this is going to work?

1318
01:14:43,710 --> 01:14:46,670
No, this has to work.
No margin for error.

1319
01:14:49,430 --> 01:14:51,510
TARDIS THRUMS

1320
01:14:57,790 --> 01:15:01,830
Yes! Temporal hop, 106 years,
done.

1321
01:15:01,830 --> 01:15:04,470
Now...for conversion.

1322
01:15:05,790 --> 01:15:07,470
I really hope this works.

1323
01:15:36,630 --> 01:15:39,990
Did she just freeze volcanoes
into steel?

1324
01:15:39,990 --> 01:15:41,510
Yes, I did.

1325
01:15:41,510 --> 01:15:44,590
Turning multiple planet-threatening
situations into public art!

1326
01:15:44,590 --> 01:15:47,230
You're welcome.
OK, don't get cocky.

1327
01:15:47,230 --> 01:15:49,910
Now, one last thing

1328
01:15:49,910 --> 01:15:51,310
and we're done.

1329
01:15:53,510 --> 01:15:55,350
Do you think we can let go yet?

1330
01:15:56,830 --> 01:15:58,750
DOCTOR: I'm sorry
for what was done to you.

1331
01:15:58,750 --> 01:16:01,150
I'm sorry that you were taken
and that you've been harnessed.

1332
01:16:01,150 --> 01:16:03,030
I'll see you released.

1333
01:16:03,030 --> 01:16:05,070
But I need one more thing
from you.

1334
01:16:05,070 --> 01:16:07,910
Channel your energy
down into this planet.

1335
01:16:07,910 --> 01:16:09,710
Disintegrate everything.

1336
01:16:09,710 --> 01:16:11,470
And then you'll be free!

1337
01:16:14,550 --> 01:16:16,790
Yes, that's it!

1338
01:16:16,790 --> 01:16:19,110
What a creature!

1339
01:16:19,110 --> 01:16:20,710
What a universe!

1340
01:16:21,790 --> 01:16:23,310
I'll never understand it.

1341
01:16:31,270 --> 01:16:33,710
HE YELLS

1342
01:16:33,710 --> 01:16:35,470
HE GROANS

1343
01:16:43,110 --> 01:16:44,390
MASTER: Doctor!

1344
01:16:47,670 --> 01:16:49,950
You lost.

1345
01:16:51,550 --> 01:16:54,070
You gambled and you lost.

1346
01:16:54,070 --> 01:16:56,430
And now your body is failing
because of

1347
01:16:56,430 --> 01:16:59,030
what you put it through.
Maybe.

1348
01:16:59,030 --> 01:17:01,150
But if I can't be the Doctor...

1349
01:17:06,670 --> 01:17:08,150
..neither can you.

1350
01:17:10,750 --> 01:17:12,390
SHE SHOUTS

1351
01:17:56,230 --> 01:17:57,590
She's fine.

1352
01:17:57,590 --> 01:17:58,710
She's fine!

1353
01:18:03,310 --> 01:18:05,590
DOCTOR GASPS SOFTLY

1354
01:18:12,270 --> 01:18:13,990
Extended fam.

1355
01:18:22,070 --> 01:18:24,510
RUMBLING

1356
01:18:26,230 --> 01:18:28,310
TARDIS THRUMS

1357
01:18:44,390 --> 01:18:46,230
Did we do it?

1358
01:18:49,910 --> 01:18:51,670
We did it.

1359
01:18:51,670 --> 01:18:53,630
Well, you did it.

1360
01:18:58,350 --> 01:18:59,750
Where is everyone?

1361
01:18:59,750 --> 01:19:03,270
I took them home.
Did you?

1362
01:19:04,390 --> 01:19:06,430
That's clever.
Well...

1363
01:19:07,710 --> 01:19:10,910
..Croydon, so close enough.

1364
01:19:13,670 --> 01:19:15,230
How long was I out?

1365
01:19:17,150 --> 01:19:18,390
A while.

1366
01:19:20,430 --> 01:19:22,910
CLOISTER BELL RINGS

1367
01:19:22,910 --> 01:19:25,430
DOCTOR GASPS

1368
01:19:26,910 --> 01:19:28,870
Why's the Cloister Bell ringing?

1369
01:19:28,870 --> 01:19:30,190
Doctor...

1370
01:19:30,190 --> 01:19:31,750
Look at your hand.

1371
01:19:33,470 --> 01:19:35,510
CLOISTER BELL CONTINUES RINGING

1372
01:19:35,510 --> 01:19:37,110
No!

1373
01:19:37,110 --> 01:19:38,950
SOFTLY: No.

1374
01:19:38,950 --> 01:19:40,710
That's not right.

1375
01:19:40,710 --> 01:19:42,630
I need more time.

1376
01:19:45,750 --> 01:19:47,270
I want more time!

1377
01:19:47,270 --> 01:19:48,430
CRIES OUT

1378
01:19:53,910 --> 01:19:55,390
You know what this means, right?

1379
01:19:58,070 --> 01:19:59,190
Yeah?

1380
01:20:00,710 --> 01:20:02,550
It's all right.

1381
01:20:02,550 --> 01:20:04,350
It's all right, Yaz.

1382
01:20:07,350 --> 01:20:09,110
One last trip.

1383
01:20:10,830 --> 01:20:12,910
Where would you choose?

1384
01:20:14,670 --> 01:20:16,430
What flavour ice cream?

1385
01:20:16,430 --> 01:20:18,190
BOTH LAUGH

1386
01:20:18,190 --> 01:20:20,230
CLOISTER BELL CONTINUES RINGING

1387
01:20:36,150 --> 01:20:38,870
How many times do you think
you've saved Earth?

1388
01:20:38,870 --> 01:20:40,590
I've lost count.

1389
01:20:42,230 --> 01:20:43,630
But look at it.

1390
01:20:43,630 --> 01:20:46,390
How could you not love
a planet like that?

1391
01:20:50,710 --> 01:20:52,270
I don't want it to end.

1392
01:21:01,470 --> 01:21:03,950
A wise person once said to me...

1393
01:21:03,950 --> 01:21:06,790
..goodbyes only hurt

1394
01:21:06,790 --> 01:21:09,430
because what came before
was so special.

1395
01:21:10,630 --> 01:21:12,670
Oh, and it's been so special.

1396
01:21:14,990 --> 01:21:16,710
You...

1397
01:21:16,710 --> 01:21:20,310
..and Graham...and Ryan...
and Dan.

1398
01:21:21,550 --> 01:21:23,990
Nobody else got to be us.

1399
01:21:25,710 --> 01:21:27,990
Nobody else got to live our days.

1400
01:21:30,070 --> 01:21:31,230
Nobody.

1401
01:21:32,550 --> 01:21:35,510
And my hearts are so full of love

1402
01:21:35,510 --> 01:21:36,950
of all of you.

1403
01:21:40,990 --> 01:21:45,270
Oh, I have loved
being with you, Yaz.

1404
01:21:47,950 --> 01:21:50,030
And I have loved being me.

1405
01:21:58,870 --> 01:22:01,430
I think I need to
do this next bit alone.

1406
01:22:12,230 --> 01:22:13,750
Let's not say goodbye.

1407
01:22:59,750 --> 01:23:01,870
TARDIS THRUMS

1408
01:23:03,550 --> 01:23:05,870
DISTANT ARGUING

1409
01:23:07,190 --> 01:23:09,910
GRAHAM: Look, it's definitely left,
not right.

1410
01:23:09,910 --> 01:23:11,470
DAN: Mate, I know
how to read a map.

1411
01:23:11,470 --> 01:23:13,630
Yeah, I understand that,
but...let me have a look.

1412
01:23:13,630 --> 01:23:16,830
I've got it here!
Just let me, please.

1413
01:23:17,830 --> 01:23:18,950
BOTH: Yaz!

1414
01:23:22,110 --> 01:23:23,230
How...? How is she?

1415
01:23:23,230 --> 01:23:24,350
How was she?

1416
01:23:25,390 --> 01:23:26,910
What are you doing here?

1417
01:23:28,710 --> 01:23:30,190
Didn't you get your invite?

1418
01:23:31,630 --> 01:23:33,950
I'm Graham. And...

1419
01:23:33,950 --> 01:23:37,030
..apparently I've got to be
the first one to talk, so...

1420
01:23:37,030 --> 01:23:39,350
CLEARS HIS THROAT

1421
01:23:37,030 --> 01:23:39,350
Right.

1422
01:23:39,350 --> 01:23:40,950
I have this problem.

1423
01:23:42,030 --> 01:23:43,430
See, I met this person,

1424
01:23:43,430 --> 01:23:46,830
and I got whooshed away
across all space and time.

1425
01:23:46,830 --> 01:23:48,990
I mean, I had the most amazing
adventures, really.

1426
01:23:48,990 --> 01:23:51,950
I mean, you wait till you hear,
cos I'm going to tell you 'em all.

1427
01:23:51,950 --> 01:23:53,550
LAUGHTER

1428
01:23:51,950 --> 01:23:53,550
But... But I came back,

1429
01:23:53,550 --> 01:23:55,230
and I actually can't tell anyone,

1430
01:23:55,230 --> 01:23:58,070
because...they'd have me put away.

1431
01:23:58,070 --> 01:23:59,430
LAUGHTER

1432
01:23:59,430 --> 01:24:02,350
And that's... That started me
thinking, though.

1433
01:24:02,350 --> 01:24:05,110
"I can't be the only one.
I can't."

1434
01:24:05,110 --> 01:24:06,870
And look! I'm not.

1435
01:24:08,790 --> 01:24:11,270
I reckon there are more people
out there too.

1436
01:24:12,270 --> 01:24:16,390
So maybe this is
where we share stories...

1437
01:24:16,390 --> 01:24:18,510
TARDIS THRUMS

1438
01:24:16,390 --> 01:24:18,510
..about the Doc.

1439
01:24:19,830 --> 01:24:23,070
I will also say...I may want
to recruit you for some work.

1440
01:24:23,070 --> 01:24:25,390
LAUGHTER

1441
01:24:26,550 --> 01:24:27,630
Dan.

1442
01:24:27,630 --> 01:24:29,430
I've, er...

1443
01:24:29,430 --> 01:24:32,350
I've only been back a month, and...

1444
01:24:32,350 --> 01:24:34,350
..I've got to say, I'm glad

1445
01:24:34,350 --> 01:24:38,230
I'm not on the verge of
being exterminated any more.

1446
01:24:38,230 --> 01:24:39,630
LAUGHTER

1447
01:24:40,630 --> 01:24:42,150
But I do miss her.

1448
01:24:43,910 --> 01:24:46,670
Sorry...did you say...

1449
01:24:47,950 --> 01:24:49,750
..her?

1450
01:24:50,790 --> 01:24:52,350
How many Doctors are there?

1451
01:24:52,350 --> 01:24:55,390
I think we're going to be here
quite some time.

1452
01:24:59,870 --> 01:25:01,830
Look after the next one.

1453
01:25:01,830 --> 01:25:03,470
You OK?

1454
01:25:04,750 --> 01:25:06,430
Is she OK?

1455
01:25:09,270 --> 01:25:11,070
Going to take in one last sunrise.

1456
01:25:13,910 --> 01:25:15,190
Of course she's OK.

1457
01:25:16,950 --> 01:25:18,990
She's the Doctor.

1458
01:25:30,350 --> 01:25:33,230
BIRDS CALL, WAVES LAP

1459
01:25:35,710 --> 01:25:37,470
Oh, the blossomiest blossom.

1460
01:25:42,710 --> 01:25:44,390
That's the only sad thing.

1461
01:25:47,630 --> 01:25:49,470
I want to know what happens next.

1462
01:25:52,430 --> 01:25:53,670
Right, then.

1463
01:25:56,190 --> 01:25:58,150
Doctor Whoever-I'm-about-to-be...

1464
01:25:59,630 --> 01:26:01,030
..tag,

1465
01:26:01,030 --> 01:26:02,470
you're it.

1466
01:26:33,870 --> 01:26:35,630
HE GASPS

1467
01:26:38,390 --> 01:26:39,950
I know these teeth.

1468
01:26:45,670 --> 01:26:47,070
What?

1469
01:26:49,990 --> 01:26:51,110
What?

1470
01:26:56,310 --> 01:26:57,670
What?!

